title: pink punch(very good)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in one cup of hot water.
Set aside.
Mix Kool-Aid in 4 quarts of water.
Add 4 cups sugar.
Add other juices, then add Jell-O mixture.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir well.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with bread crumbs.
Bake casserole at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: To make 16 six-inch pastries, preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a cookie sheet and set aside.

title: cold potato salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix the sour cream, salad dressing, sweet relish, mustard and sugar in bowl. Add to potato mixture; mix well.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: southern pralines
directions: Combine sugar and soda in deep 3-quart pan.
Mix well with wooden spoon, adding evaporated milk.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook to 234° (soft ball stage). Remove from heat; add margarine and pecans.
Beat until thick. Drop on wax paper.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large
bowl,
mix liquids together.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°. Check
with
toothpick
for doneness.
Makes 2 one-pound loaves.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in ungreased square pan.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over.
Bake for 40 minutes.
While warm, spoon into dishes and top with ice cream.
Spoon sauce from pan onto each serving.

title: yam casserole
directions: Combine yams with remaining ingredients, except marshmallows. Place in buttered casserole. Push marshmallows down into mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt the Hershey bar in the Hershey's syrup and set aside to cool.

Cream the oleo and sugar until light. Add each egg separately, beating after each addition. Add the chocolate and vanilla to the egg mixture. To this, alternately add the flour, which has been mixed with the soda
and salt, and the buttermilk.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or longer, if needed.
(This cake is very moist and sweet and doesn't need to be iced.)

title: eggnog ala bailey's
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together, mixing very well with electric mixer.
Add ice cream and milk and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and Bailey's.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together and bake at 400° for 20 minutes in regular muffin tins.
Bake 10 minutes in small tins.
Batter and muffins freeze well.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a slow cooker.
Cook 4 to 6 hours.

title: oven crusted chicken
directions: Combine margarine, flour and seasonings and blend well. Dip chicken pieces in this mixture, then in cereal crumbs. Place coated chicken on greased baking sheet. Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes. Then turn and bake 25 minutes longer or until crisp and brown. Serves 4.

title: molasses cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix.
Add molasses, oil and boiling water, mixing well.
Add spices and flour; mix well.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: springele
directions: Add powdered sugar to eggs and beat for 20 minutes.
Mix in flour, baking powder and anise seed or oil.
Roll out and cut and let lay overnight.
Bake at 300°.

title: mandarin pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a medium mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add boiling water, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in orange juice, sweetener and orange peel.
Beat in yogurt until thoroughly mixed.
Refrigerate about 45 minutes, until partially set.
Fold in orange sections.
Taste for sweetener and add more, if desired.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Refrigerate about 4 hours, until set.
Other fruits can be used, if desired.
Contains 16 g carbohydrates, 3 g protein, 8 g fat and 148 calories.

title: chinese turkey salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients in bowl; whisk well to make vinaigrette.
Drizzle in the peanut and sesame oils, whisking until dressing is slightly thick.
Toss turkey and pepper with 1/3 cup of dressing.
Reserve remaining dressing for another use.

title: red hot cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in large stock pot.
Heat on medium until candies have melted.
Discard spices.
Serve hot.
Makes 20 to 25 servings.

title: microwave lemon pie
directions: In bowl safe for microwave, put in sugar, salt and cornstarch mix.
Add lemon juice and eggs.
Beat well.
Add 1/2 cup water. Beat again.
Add the other 2 cups water and food coloring.
Beat again, then put in microwave for 2 minutes.
Take out and beat.
Do this for around 8 minutes.
Beat after every 2 minutes.
It is important to beat it good and be sure to stir it good off the bottom.
Beat in oleo.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix butter and graham crackers until moist and then pack in ungreased 8 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch glass casserole dish.
Mix Dream Whip as directed.
Add cream cheese; blend until smooth.
Then add gradually powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Spoon filling over graham cracker crust.
Spoon pie filling on top of cheese filling.
Let stand in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.

title: mama's cabbage-pepper relish
directions: Chop cabbage, peppers and carrots; mix with salt and let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Boil vinegar, sugar and spices.
Pour over chopped vegetables and boil 25 minutes.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine in bowl and mix well the zucchini, cheese, spices and Bisquick.
Add beaten eggs.
Melt butter.
Pour all into 8-inch square Pyrex dish.
Top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test for firmness.

title: sauce (creme dijon)
directions: In a small saucepan, beat all ingredients until smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture begins to thicken.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.
Serve with beef, poultry, fish and vegetables.

title: play doh surprise
directions: In a saucepan mix flour, salt, cream of tartar and oil. Stir all together until smooth
with
a
wire whip.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly
with
a
large spoon until a ball forms, about 5 minutes.
Turn out on wax paper until cool enough to handle.
Knead.
Store
in
plastic
bag
or tightly covered container.

title: singing chicken(ga kho)
directions: Steam rice and set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic to oil and stir-fry for about 1 minute.
Add the chicken and stir-fry for about 5 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook, stirring often, until the chicken is cooked and the sauce is slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Serve hot with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread
bottom of a large glass pan with refried beans; top with sour cream.
Top
with
taco
sauce; top with cheese, then onions, olives and tomatoes last.
Chill, then serve with chips.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to boil; boil for 2 minutes. Then add vanilla, peanut butter and quick oats.
Beat.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix beef, sausage and spaghetti sauce.
Set aside.
Mix together cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Set aside.

title: santa whiskers
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour alternately with milk. Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Dough should be stiff.
Blend in cherries and nuts by hand.
Make logs 5-inches and roll in Angel Flake coconut.
Wrap in wax paper; chill.
Slice off 1/4-inch slices and place on cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
They do not spread. Bake at 375° until golden brown, approximately 7 minutes.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Beat all together and bake at 350° in a lightly greased Bundt pan or a tube pan for about 55 minutes.

title: sugar-free fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

In a baking dish, melt the margarine. In a mixing bowl, combine the baking mix and milk. Stir well. Pour over the melted margarine. Spread the fruit over the mixture. Bake 1 hour or until done.	Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: chop suey hors d'oeuvres
directions: Brown hamburger in small amount of margarine; drain fat.
Add dry soup mix to hamburger.
Chop water chestnuts.
Add bean sprouts and water chestnuts to hamburger mix.
Stir in soy sauce and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: meatballs for spaghetti or subs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into golf ball size balls and brown in microwave oven or skillet.
Drain liquid and add to spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti noodles or on hoagie buns and top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients. Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Turn on a wire rack to cool.

title: homemade butter pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt.
Roll 1 teaspoon dough into ball and dip in slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Place on baking sheet and press thumb in middle.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Let cool and fill the center with filling.
Refrigerate after a couple of days.

title: french fried vegetables
directions: Clean desired vegetables and cut into slices about 1/2-inch thick, then cut into strips as you would potatoes for French fries.
Cover with buttermilk and soak for a while.
Drain and batter with flour.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown. Vegetables will be more crisp if you wait until you remove them from the oil to salt.
Drain on paper towel.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring pineapple and Jell-O to a boil.
Stir until dissolved.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Mix well in bowl.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour 1 1/2 cups pecans around bottom of pan.
Pour batter over pecans.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
When cake is done, mix the following in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Poke holes in cake with fork while cake is still hot in pan.
Pour over cake.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: Place bread crumbs in 1-quart baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs and toss to coat.
Mix tomatoes, brown sugar and salt.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Mix gently and bake in 425 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: hazelnut balls
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Beat until frothy the egg whites.
Add about 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition the sugar.
Continue beating the meringue until stiff peaks are formed.
Fold the hazelnuts into the meringue mixture.
Shape dough into balls about 1/2-inch in diameter. Place on the cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
With a spatula, carefully remove cookies from cookie sheets to cooling racks.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: pickled tomatoes
directions: Boil water, salt, vinegar, dill seed and celery seed for 5 minutes.
Pour over fruit and seal.
Let stand 4 to 6 weeks.
Pack jars and set in hot water before pouring hot solution in jar (prevents breaking and seals better).
Fill with small or pieces of green tomatoes.
Cucumbers can be used instead or mixed with tomatoes.
A sprig of fresh dill can be used.
Also, two hot peppers may be added if desired.
Solution for 6 quarts.

title: shrimp and scallops fajitas
directions: Mix Cajun seasoning, oil, lime juice, oregano, cumin and garlic in shallow glass or plastic dish.
Stir in shrimp and scallops.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: low-fat chicken chowder
directions: In a saucepan, combine chicken, water, onion, carrot, bouillon granules, garlic and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in potato.
Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes more or until chicken and potato are tender.
Remove chicken.
When cool enough to handle, cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Return to saucepan.
Mash potato slightly.
Combine milk and cornstarch; add to saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Ladle into soup bowls; sprinkle with chives.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pear preserves
directions: Place sliced pears and sugar in pan in layers.	Let stand about 1 hour or until sugar melts to make syrup.	Cook on low heat until pears are tender and done.	Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: cheese and spinach crustless quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and half and half cream together.
Blend in cheese, spinach, bacon bit, salt and lemon juice.
Place in 9-inch quiche or pie pan, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into 10 wedges.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion, salt and pepper in 1/2 cup water slowly until most of the water is gone.
Drain.
Add sour cream, Worcestershire, eggs and 1/2 of cracker crumbs.
Add cheese and pimento; stir well.

title: three bean salad
directions: Bring to boil the oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over beans, pepper and onion.
Stir and marinate for 24 hours.

title: baked spring rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir-fry the ginger in hot oils for 30 seconds.
Add next 6 ingredients and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add soy sauce and cornstarch mixture.
Stir until slightly thickened. Remove and cool.
Cut each phyllo sheet in half (7 x 18-inch) with narrow side facing you.
Brush with butter and place 2 tablespoons filling 1-inch from bottom.
Fold sides to cover filling.
Brush long side with butter and roll up.
Repeat process with remaining phyllo and filling.
Refrigerate or freeze until ready to use. Before serving, brush with butter and sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve immediately.

title: easy vegetable quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate or quiche dish. Cook and drain broccoli or put frozen broccoli into greased pie plate.
Sprinkle onion, green pepper and cheese over it.
Blend remaining ingredients in the blender.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake until golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting or put vegetables in night before.
Refrigerate.
Add remaining ingredients in morning and bake.
Delicious!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together; mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook cut ziti for 10 minutes; drain.
In large bowl, combine ziti, 1 1/2 cups sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella, parsley, egg, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Into a 3-quart casserole, pour 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Spread the ziti mixture evenly over the sauce. Top with remaining 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: homestyle chili
directions: Cook bacon, keeping drippings.	Crumble bacon and place in large
tall
pot.
Cook
onions until soft in bacon grease. Place in	pot.
Brown
ground beef and add beans, tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring all to a boil over medium heat; reduce heat and simmer for 4 hours.
Keep pot covered.

title: mocha truffles
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate.
Add milk, salt, coffee and liqueur.
Mix well until smooth.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
With hands dusted in cocoa, roll each into a ball.
Refrigerate.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mock crab balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls size of walnuts.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place crushed Teddy Grahams and butter to form a crust.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread 1/3 of this mixture over graham cracker crust.
Place sliced bananas over cream cheese mixture until covered.
Follow with strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Spread some of the cream cheese mixture over the fruit.
Layer again with fruit.
Top with last of cream cheese mixture.
Then top with crushed Teddy Grahams, chopped nuts and coconut to your taste. Decorate with cherries.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Cream together vanilla wafers, butter and walnuts.
Press half of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Mix together cream cheese, milk, powdered sugar.
Spread cream cheese mixture on cookie layer.
Spread rest of cookie mixture on top.
Spread a generous layer of Cool Whip.
Top with pie filling.
Also works well with blueberry or strawberry filling.
Doubled recipe fits lasagne pan.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix and make into balls and fry.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Cool.
Remove meat from bones.
Melt butter; stir in stuffing.
In large oblong baking dish, put a layer of crumbs, a layer of chicken, mushroom soup (diluted with chicken broth), then another layer of chicken and the chicken soup (diluted with broth).
Top with crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: nutty buddy pies
directions: Beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar and milk in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shells.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Yield:
18 servings.

title: pecan pie ii
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken mauter
directions: Mix ingredients.
Baste chicken with mixture.
Roast at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: tomato sauce for meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat over low heat stirring until all ingredients come together to a creamy consistency.
Serve over your meat loaf or as a dipping sauce.

title: unstuffed pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Set aside.
In saucepan, heat water and butter to simmer.
Add sage and onion stuffing and unpeeled apple. Stir lightly until moisture is absorbed.
Spoon stuffing into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Arrange chops over stuffing. Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: herbed stuffed snow peas
directions: Break ends off of snow peas and pull string from straight side of peas.
Blanch peas in boiling water for 1 minute.
Remove from water immediately and pour peas into a bowl of ice water.
Mix cream with Boursin cheese and put mixture in a pastry bag.
Slit the straight side of peas to open and pipe cheese mixture into peas.
Arrange on a plate and serve well-chilled.

title: fudge melt-aways
directions: Melt 1 sq. chocolate and 1/2 c. butter.
Mix in sugar, 1 tsp. vanilla, egg, graham cracker crumbs, coconut, and nuts.
Press into baking dish and chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Blend well.
Add eggs one at a time. Blend well.
Add flour and baking powder to mixture.
Then add milk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: butter rolls
directions: Combine milk, 1 cup sugar and vanilla in deep Corning Ware dish (or any baking dish).
Let get hot on top of stove.
Make biscuit dough using 1 cup sweet milk.
Let rise about 30 minutes, then work down and roll out like pie crust.
Spread about 1/2 of pound box whipped margarine over dough; sprinkle 1 cup sugar over margarine. Roll up like jelly roll and cut 1/2-inch blocks and put in hot milk, turning cut sides up.
Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes at 275°.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream and spread into pie plate. Layer the rest of the ingredients.
Serve with taco chips.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Use a piece of Reynolds Wrap.
Spray with Pam or use oil.
Put potato, a cut up piece of bacon, cheese, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper on the foil.
Put on grill or fire for 1/2 to 1 hour, until tender.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken and sun dried tomatoes with fettucini
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving oil.
Coarsely chop tomatoes and set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon reserved oil from tomatoes in a large skillet.
Saute onion and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Add chicken and saute 8 minutes or until tender.
Add basil and reserved tomatoes; saute an additional 2 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and an additional 2 tablespoons reserved oil from the dried tomatoes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixer bowl; mix until smooth. Spoon into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove and cool on wire rack to cool.

title: blond brownies
directions: Mix eggs, softened butter and brown sugar. Next add the salt, flour, baking powder, soda and vanilla; mix well. Add the chocolate chips. Pour into an 8 x 12 baking pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and cut into squares. Makes 12 bars.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine, dressing mix, mustard and garlic until smooth and creamy.
Hollow out bread and pour mixture into the hollowed hole.
Take bread from the hole and cut into strips for dipping.

title: eggplant cheese puffs
directions: Cook eggplant 10 to 15 minutes; drain and mash.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Blend well and chill for 1 hour.
Form mix into bite size balls, roll in flour.
Fry puffs in olive oil.
Drain on paper towels.
To freeze, place on tray and freeze; put in Baggies when frozen.
To serve, bake on cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and form into loaf.

title: brownie muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, cocoa and cinnamon.
Make well in center.
Combine egg, oil and milk.
Add to dry ingredients in well; stir until moistened.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 12.

title: butter herb baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine crackers, cheese and spices.
Dip fish in butter, then in crumb mixture.
Arrange fish in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Serves 4.

title: german potato salad
directions: Heat thoroughly, tossing lightly. Garnish with parsley and bacon curls.

title: sinful baked fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in a bowl over hot water.
Work half of the sugar into the egg yolks, stirring with a whisk until mixture lightens in color.
Combine yolk mixture with chocolate mixture.
Whip egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually add the remaining sugar to make a stiff meringue.
Fold into chocolate batter carefully, preserving as much volume as possible.
Chill to set, approximately 3 hours.
Smooth one-half batter into a greased 9 x 12 baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool (it will fall).
When cool, smooth remaining batter into the same pan and freeze solid, 3 hours or overnight.
Bake 20-30 minutes at 400 degrees until center is hot, but still liquid and fudge is cakey on top and bottom.
Serve warm with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Saute onion in butter.
Add hash browns, soup, sour cream.
Mix well.
Spoon into 9x13 casserole.
Sprinkle bag of cheese over potato mixture, then top with crushed corn flakes.

title: brandy chicken
directions: Lightly dredge breasts in flour.
Lightly brown in 3 to 4 tablespoons butter.
Put in single layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy miniature meatballs
directions: *If you use spicy barbecue sauce or salsa, sauce will have more of a kick.

title: painted dessert
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water; stir in 1/2 cup ginger ale.
Set aside 1 cup gelatin and chill until thickened (1 hour).
Stir in 1/2 cup Cool Whip into remaining dissolved gelatin; chill until thickened.
Repeat with orange then strawberry gel.
Pretty when put in clear bowl.
Most children love this because there isn't anything in the jello (fruit, etc.).

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel baked sweet potatoes.
Mix all ingredients and put in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meringue that won't weep
directions: Cook cornstarch, 2 tablespoons sugar and water together until clear; set aside to cool.
Mixture will be stiff.
Beat egg whites until it stands in a peak.
Add cornstarch mixture; beat until creamy.
Continue beating and gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar, the vanilla and salt.
Beat until creamy.
Can be used on anything that calls for meringue.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain and mash squash.
Add all remaining ingredients except 1/2 of the butter.
Pour into baking dish.
Pour remaining butter over top.
Sprinkle with additional cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Combine sugar, milk and water.
Bring to a boil about 3 to 4 minutes (until soft ball forms in water).
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir mixture until thick.
Pour on wax paper and separate.

title: chocolate peanut treats
directions: In a bowl, combine cracker crumbs and butter; mix well. Stir in sugar and peanut butter. Press into greased 8-inch square pan. In a microwave or double boiler, melt the chocolate chips and stir until smooth. Spread over peanut butter layer. Chill for 30 minutes. Cut in squares. Chill until firm, about 30 minutes longer. Store in refrigerator.

title: chestnut rumaki
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Pour into skillet.
Add butter, simmer over low heat for about 5 minutes. Add carrots and cook over moderate heat for 15 minutes, basting frequently.
Serves 4 - 6.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix white sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a bowl.
Roll biscuit dough out, cut in fourths.
Roll in sugar mixture. Arrange in Bundt pan; sprinkle nuts through mixture.
In small saucepan, mix the margarine, brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Pour this mixture over the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Turn out on plate; serve warm.
Pulls apart.

title: pretzel congealed salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine pretzels, margarine, and 3 Tbsp. sugar and mix well. Bake in a 9x13 inch pan for 10 minutes. Cool completely. Cream the cheese and blend in 1 cup sugar. Add the whipped topping, mixing well. Spread over the cooled pretzels. Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water. Add the frozen strawberries, breaking up with a fork as you stir. Chill until slightly thickened. Pour over whipped topping layer, chill until set.

title: pineapple cheese mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and pepper with ice water with 2 tablespoons canning salt.
Let set 1 hour, then drain.
Boil all ingredients for 10 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: boneless chicken with corn flakes
directions: Place chicken in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soup, onion, mayonnaise and milk together.
Spread over chicken.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine and mix with 1/2 cup of corn flake crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of each piece of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix well cream cheese, vinegar, onion, celery, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Add shrimp.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate in bowl.
Make small balls.
Freeze. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: party wieners
directions: Stuffed olives crown a pretty double-molded spread of meat and cheese.
Makes 25 servings.

title: family favorite salad
directions: Heat Jell-O in water until dissolved.
Add marshmallows and cook until melted.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Cool until set.

title: cranberry spread
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese, powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in cranberries.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Heat the marshmallows, candy bars and milk over medium-low heat until melted.
Cool to room temperature.
Whip one cup whipping cream and fold into cooled chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze and then top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Mix lightly, but well.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, baking powder, allspice and nutmeg; mix together.
Divide batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: jalapeno rice casserole
directions: Combine water and bouillon in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat.
Stir in yogurt, salad dressing, pepper and cilantro.
Spoon into 1-quart dish coated with spray. Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine. Mix rice, onion, celery and raw broccoli. Add soup, salt, pepper and Cheez Whiz.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Top with grated cheese, if desired. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift 2 cups flour and powdered sugar together.
Cut in margarine until well blended.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on cooled crust.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cover with powdered sugar while still warm.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine in Dutch oven the broccoli, American cheese, chicken broth, Parmesan cheese and sour cream.
Cook until hot.
Add noodles and chicken.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° to 400° for about 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: meme's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco together.
Slowly add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Add batter.
Place in a cold oven.
Set temperature at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn down to 325° for 1 hour.

title: blackened fish
directions: Use iron skillet, gas cooker, fish cooker or any type of cooker that requires a high heat.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine flour and sugar; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well. Press onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: creamy green vegetable casserole
directions: Cook broccoli
using package directions, adding 2 beef bouillon cubes, salt and pepper to cooking water; drain.
Cook lima beans using package directions, adding 1 beef bouillon cube to cooking water; drain.
Combine broccoli, lima beans, water chestnuts, sour cram and mushroom soup in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with mixture of cereal and melted margarine.
Bake at 325 to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly and browned.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Blend mayonnaise with lemon juice, onion and salt.
Mix lightly with chicken, celery and almonds.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May be served on a bed of lettuce or watercress.
You may also make this using either cooked shrimp, turkey or crabmeat in place of chicken.

title: burger bundles
directions: Mix stuffing as directed.
Mix ground beef with milk.
Divide into 5 patties.
Flatten to form a circle with each patty.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in middle of each patty.
Draw up edges of meat and seal.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° until done, about 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Grind cranberries and orange (including rind) in blender, small portions at a time.
Add sugar.
Mix well with fruit and let it sit 1 hour. When Jell-O begins to congeal, add fruit.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Place in refrigerator.
Cut in squares to serve over a lettuce leaf.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice 2 or 3 small zucchini in a casserole dish.
Cover above mixture with 1 - 29 oz. can Hunt's tomato sauce.

title: chess bars
directions: Melt oleo and cool. Add beaten eggs and oleo to cake mix. Spread in thin layer over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Layer ingredients:
cabbage, peas and carrots (thawed), chicken and green onions.
Chill.
Put noodles (broken up) on salad just before tossing with dressing.

title: pineberry smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and serve.

title: easy bar-b-que chicken(or cola surprise chicken)
directions: Cut chicken in desired pieces, salt and pepper chicken.
Mix ketchup and coke in skillet, place chicken in skillet.
Cook slowly until tender, turning occasionally.
The juice cooks down to a thick sauce.
Very good.

title: onion casserole bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter. Cool to lukewarm. Measure water in a bowl and sprinkle in the yeast. Stir to dissolve and add the cooled milk mixture.
Add the onions and flour.
Stir until well blended, about 2 minutes. Cover and let rise until dough has doubled (about 1 hour).
Stir down and beat 1 minute. Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish. Bake about 1
hour at 375°.

title: christmas jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Make up jello according to package directions, but using pineapple juice for part of the water.
While jello is still warm, add cream cheese and beat with mixer until cheese is dissolved; add mayonnaise and beat until frothy.
Dice cherries and add to jello mixture along with pineapple and nuts.
Mix well and turn into a 2-quart mold.
Stir once or twice so pineapple and nuts don't all rise to the top.

title: speedy oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir until smooth the first 7 ingredients. Add flour, oatmeal and nuts. Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in a 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Spaghetti Sauce:
Chop the red and green peppers and onion into a saucepan.
Saute slowly.
Add tomato paste, 2 cans of water and tomato sauce.
Stir together and simmer for approximately 6 to 10 minutes.
Season to taste with basil, garlic powder, oregano and bay leaves.
Add a teaspoon of sugar; simmer for 5 minutes.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Cook bacon.
Add to other ingredients in crock-pot.
Season with salt.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: peanut butter play dough(you can eat it.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill, play and eat.

title: cheese cake
directions: To soft cream cheese add sugar.
Add one egg at a time; beat after each egg.
Add milk; beat.
Add sour cream; beat.
Add flour and vanilla; beat.
Grease a spring-form baking pan.
Pour in mixed ingredients.
Bake one (1) hour at 370° or until golden brown. Leave in oven one (1) hour after baked.
Cool two hours.

title: strawberry torte
directions: Combine flour and margarine and mix well.
Add pecans and press mixture in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Knead.
Roll on floured dough board real thin.
Dry about 2 hours. Drop in boiling broth with chicken, removed of skin and deboned. Makes 4 servings.

title: maple spread
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar together.
Put evaporated milk into measuring cup and add water to bring it to 1 cup.
Put all ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil, stirring often.
When it starts to thicken, remove from heat.
Great on toast!

title: caramel bars
directions: Combine dry cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, butter and nuts.
Put 3/4 mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: red potatoes and garlic
directions: Dice potatoes in 1-inch cubes.
Mince garlic finely.
Add potatoes to a shallow baking dish; top with remaining ingredients, dotting butter over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on English muffin halves, then cut each half into 4 pieces.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: beef ravioli soup
directions: In a kettle, saute celery, onion and carrots in oil for 3 minutes; add broth and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 15 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Stir in the ravioli and heat through.
Garnish with parsley and Parmesan cheese.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Stir cornmeal into boiling salted water.
Stir for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add butter; beat well.
Add eggs.
Beat in cold milk.
Beat again.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve from dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain; set aside.
Mix soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese.
Add to broccoli and pour into casserole dish.
Mix the crushed crackers with melted butter for topping, if desired; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german cheese pie
directions: Mix in bowl; roll into balls and flatten into 10-inch pie plate.

title: easy homemade donuts
directions: Need little saucepan.
Put 1/3 full of oil.
Heat; when hot, place a biscuit (with hole in middle) in pan.
Cook until light brown; turn and cook other side.
After they're out place in powdered sugar or cinnamon sugar mixture.
Serve while warm.

title: cheesy grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to package.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, pepper and cheese until melted.
Stir 1 cup hot mixture into egg yolks.
Stir the egg yolks mixture into remaining grits. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into grits.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle paprika over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 30 minutes, until puffed.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Grate cheese over top and serve.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Save a few shrimp out for garnish.
Mix cream cheese, shrimp, 1/4 cup shrimp juice and Worcestershire sauce together.
Shape into ball and pour cocktail sauce over.
Add garnish shrimp. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars together.
Add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Beat in flour and oatmeal.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake on cookie sheets for 9 1/2 to 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine uncooked hamburger with remaining ingredients.
Put into loaf pan that has been oiled.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: grandma cinnamon rolls
directions: Prepare or purchase your favorite yeast dough.
Roll dough out flat on the countertop until it is 1/2-inch thick.
Spread cinnamon, mixed with sugar, over the dough until the surface of the dough is covered.
With your fingers, gently roll the dough evenly into a roll and cut off 1-inch thick sections.
Put the rolls into a greased cake pan so that they have 1/2-inch between each other.
Cover the pan with a cloth and let the dough rise until it has doubled in size.
Bake the rolls for 35 to 45 minutes at 375°.
After the rolls are done, cover them with a powdered sugar glaze.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour to butter mixture; blend until smooth.
Stir in small chocolate chips.
Mold scant tablespoonful of dough around each unwrapped Kiss, covering completely.
Shape into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly; move from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Prepare Chocolate Drizzle, if desired.
Drizzle over each cookie.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: mother's coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar a little at a time. Fold in flour, coconut, vanilla and Post Toasties.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until delicately brown.
May add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: weight watchers chili
directions: Cook hamburger, onion, water and peppers together.
Add chili powder, garlic powder, tomato juice and bean sprouts and simmer for 1 hour.

title: butternut squash and apple soup
directions: Peel, seed and coarsely chop apples and squash.
Coarsely chop onion.
Combine first 10 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer uncovered 45 minutes.
Cool soup a bit, then puree in blender.
Return soup to saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add cream and, if desired, sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook sausage and onion.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients (except bread crumbs, eggs and flour).
Heat until cream cheese melts.
Refrigerate overnight (or 1 to 2 hours). Roll into balls.
Roll balls in flour, dip in eggs (add 1 or 2 tablespoons water to eggs), then roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: polish sausage and cabbage
directions: Slice sausage and lightly brown in skillet.
Remove sausage and add onion and cabbage and cook for approximately 5 minutes. Return sausage to skillet.
Sprinkle sugar, salt and pepper over mixture; toss and coat.
Then add vinegar, water and cornstarch mixture and simmer 20 to 30 minutes in a loosely covered skillet.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until thick and foamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Stir in salt, pecans and chocolate chips. Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by tablespoon onto foil paper on cookie sheet.
Place in oven; turn off and leave in closed oven overnight.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: Mix ingredients and serve chilled.

title: low-fat twinkie cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Twinkies.
Next layer bananas and pineapple.
Mix pudding as directed.
Pour on top, then add Cool Whip.

title: granny riggs' cornbread
directions: Place all of the ingredients in bowl and mix by hand.
Dissolve 1 level teaspoon of soda in 1/8 cup water, add to mixture.
Sift in 2 cups cake flour and beat well.
Add 1 cup boiling water, beat lightly and quickly.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: apricot muffins
directions: Soak apricots in water for 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add sour cream, mix well.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture until just moistened. Drain apricots, discarding water.
Fold into batter along with nuts.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes. Makes 12 to 18 muffins.

title: zucchini tomato salad
directions: Slice zucchini.
Chop tomato, pepper and onion.
Mix together and cover with oil and vinegar mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: diabetic chocolate cake
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Bake in a medium-sized pan at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: annette's "puppy chow" snack
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over low heat.
Pour melted mixture over Chex cereal and mix.
Put powdered sugar in a large paper bag.
Add Chex mixture to this.
Shake up in bag.
Store in airtight containers.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar.
Combine oil and orange juice and add alternately with dry ingredients to egg/sugar mixture. Mix until smooth.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Arrange half of apples over the batter.
Combine cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle half over the apples.
Top with remaining batter, apples and cinnamon/sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Allow cake to cool 1 hour before removing from pan.
Cool, apple side up, on a wire rack.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar if desired.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: mama's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar.
Cream until the mixture is fluffy.
Add egg yolks and jam to this mixture and beat until well blended.
Sift flour and measure.
Take out about 1/2 cup to use to dredge raisins.
Sift remaining flour with cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add flour mixture alternately with the buttermilk and soda.
Mix in flavored raisins, and lastly, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Reserve 2 tablespoons for the filling.
Divide the remaining batter into two 9-inch cake pans which have been lightly greased in the bottom and wax paper lined.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: creamy chicken and thyme
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large nonstick skillet.
Add 1/2 cup of broth.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes or until juices run clear, turning once.
Remove chicken from pan; keep warm.
Add remaining broth to skillet and bring to a boil; reduce heat to low.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O into boiling water.
Fold in thawed strawberries (with juice), bananas, and drained pineapple.
Pour half of mixture into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish as first layer. Refrigerate until firm (about 1 1/2 hours).
Spread sour cream evenly on top of first layer.
Gently spoon on rest of strawberry mixture.
Return to refrigerator until firm.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter sauce(topping for ice cream)
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water into a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add stick of margarine, marshmallows and peanut butter. Beat 2 minutes, then add milk.
Refrigerate leftovers.
It can be thinned with a little warm water.

title: porketta
directions: Rub all spices in by hand; let set overnight in refrigerator to blend all together.
(You can use a little bit of oil to help the spices to stick.)
Cook to cooking instructions for cooking pork (325° for 30 to 35 minutes for every pound of meat), or use a meat thermometer until it reaches 170° or well done.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in small amount of water until done. Drain.
Add all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and a small amount of margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart flat dish and sprinkle with reserved cracker crumbs. Drizzle on reserved margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. During the last few minutes, sprinkle reserved cheese on top. Serves 6 to 8.

title: butter dips or bread sticks
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in oven in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Remove pan as soon as melted.

title: apple burros
directions: Combine pie filling and next 4 ingredients in bowl; mix well. Spoon 2 tablespoons into center of each tortilla.
Fold in sides and roll to enclose filling.
Deep fry in 350° oil for 5 minutes or until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with sugar while still warm.
Yield:

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken) in saucepan until melted. Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour ingredients over chicken. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Combine stock, vegetables and seasonings in a large stock pot. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer about 45 minutes or until vegetables are well cooked.
Stir in butter and potato flakes to thicken.
Taste for seasoning, salting if desired.
Serves 6.

title: glorified bread pudding
directions: Butter bread and arrange slices in buttered baking dish about 7 x 11-inches.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour half of the mixture over bread.
Let stand until bread is soaked.
Cut through bread until it is in 1-inch pieces. Add remainder of egg mixture.
Bake about an hour at 325° or until custard is set.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl and make a trench in the center.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into trench. Stir just enough to dampen all ingredients well.
Pour into greased small loaf pans or muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Be sure to check with a toothpick and watch carefully.
Cool on rack about 6 to 10 minutes and flip out of pans.
Allow to finish cooling.
Wrap in plastic to store.
Freezes well also.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cut bacon in small strips and fry.
Cube potatoes and dice onion.
Remove bacon from skillet and place in bowl with potatoes and onion.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, vinegar and beaten egg to bacon grease and cook while stirring until thick.
Add potatoes, onion and bacon and stir until thoroughly heated.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix water and jello.
Add pineapple and pie filling mix.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan and chill until set.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and pecans.
Spread this on top of filling.
Chill.

title: green mystery punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and ginger ale together with pineapple juice.
Break up lime sherbet and add to others.
Makes 1 punch bowl.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: amish cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
If desired, flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes. Makes about 9 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into lightly greased 2 quart casserole.

title: swedish pancakes(makes 5 dozen 3-inch pancakes)
directions: Sift together in a bowl and set aside the flour, sugar and salt.
Beat in a bowl until thick the eggs.
Beat until blended the milk and melted butter.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.

title: 48 buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, shortening and sugar. Add 1 cup flour.
Mix well, add rest of flour gradually.
Knead well, let raise 1 hour and work down.
Let raise 1 hour more. Pinch off top; form buns and place on greased pans.
Cover and let raise 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and put into an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Cover the bottom and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in skillet.
Cover and cook 1 minute. Uncover and cook, turning with wide spatula, until barely tender, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and toss.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread layer of pie filling in bottom of greased pan.
Add layer of pineapple.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix, add coconut and stir well.
Spread mixture over cherries and pineapple.
Sprinkle pecans over entire cake.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: watermelon pie
directions: Stir boiling water into jello in bowl 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm. Garnish with additional whipped topping.

title: easy cheese bread
directions: Combine ingredients; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Pour into generously greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven about 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan; cool on wire cooling rack.
Makes one loaf.

title: peppermint dip
directions: Crush peppermints well and fold into the Le Creme.
Chill and serve with Pepperidge Farm chocolate laced pirouettes cookies. Very rich.

title: donut muffins
directions: Mix
well.
Sprinkle
each muffin with a combination of cinnamon and sugar.
Add a dot of butter on each muffin.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover edge of pie shell with aluminum foil strips.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes, removing foil for the last 5 minutes.
Check for doneness by inserting knife halfway between center and edge.
It should come out clean.
Cool.

title: mandarin orange cake and frosting
directions: Blend cake mix, eggs, oil and juice.
Fold in drained orange segments.
Bake in 2 (9 x 13-inch) greased and floured pans at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool completely and frost.

title: homemade buttermilk biscuits
directions: Must use these ingredients to get the right taste.

title: karen's fiesta dip
directions: Mix refried beans with taco seasoning.
Spread in deep dish pie pan.
Top with sour cream and chopped vegetables and cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pralines
directions: Put all ingredients into a large saucepan, except butter, vanilla and pecans.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils, then often enough to keep from sticking.
Cook until forms a firm, but not hard, ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until it holds shape when dropped on wax paper.

title: donna's easy salsa
directions: Chop first 7 ingredients to medium size pieces and put into food processor. Chop until pieces are smaller, adding 1/4 cup water and tomato sauce to get thickness you desired. Add garlic salt to taste. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: raisin clusters
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add raisins, sugar, egg, milk, vanilla and salt.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Add puffed wheat and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Cool slightly.
Drop by tablespoon onto coconut and roll to coat.
Cool before serving.

title: sweet and sour turnips
directions: Place turnips in saucepan.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add salt. Drain; set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Combine egg, sugar and vinegar in small mixing bowl, mixing well.
Pour into bacon and drippings.
Pour over turnip mixture.
Toss gently.

title: 7 minute fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, syrup and milk. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and boil on medium-high for 7 minutes. Remove from heat. Add margarine and vanilla. Nuts are optional.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni per package directions; drain.
Combine all ingredients except macaroni and bread and mix well.
In a casserole dish, alternate layers of macaroni with layers of mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: south dakota fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes
into 1/2-inch slices.
Beat the egg, milk and hot
pepper sauce in a shallow bowl.
Combine bread crumbs with the salt and pepper in a pie tin.

title: curried goat
directions: Coat goat with Season-All.
In large skillet, mix water, curry powder, celery and onion.
Heat on medium 4 to 5 minutes.
Add goat to skillet mixture; turn often.

title: orange supreme salad
directions: Add Jell-O vanilla pudding and tapioca pudding with water. Stir constantly over heat.
Cook until thick.
Cool thoroughly. Add Cool Whip and oranges.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: oriental chicken and cashews
directions: Heat oil in 12 x 8-inch dish at high for 2 1/2 or 3 minutes. Combine chicken, garlic, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and ginger. Add green peppers and cashews.
Place in heated oil.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on high 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until chicken and green peppers are tender.
Stir once.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.

title: the no name restaurant's fish chowder
directions: Cook finely chopped onion in butter over low heat until soft, but not brown. Cut fish into 1-inch pieces.
Place cod and water in pot with onions.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 to 4 minutes until fish flakes easily.
(Skim off any surface foam.)
Stir in evaporated milk, paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook just until all ingredients are thoroughly heated.

title: vegetable pasta bake
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Drain.
In a covered saucepan, cook broccoli, onion, pepper and garlic in small amount of water about 10 minutes until tender.
Drain.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat on high speed for 10 to 20 minutes. Can be kept for week in an airtight container on kitchen shelf or refrigerated.
To thicken or thin consistency, add more powdered sugar or more water.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans and spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350° and let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla and spread over first mixture.
Mix pudding and milk and spread over second mixture.
When ready to serve, spread on more whipped cream and sprinkle crushed Oreo cookies.

title: yum yum pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar.
Beat.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes. You may add 1/2 cup chopped pecans or coconut.

title: turnovers
directions: Mix milk, sugar, egg and nutmeg.
Mix vinegar and soda.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix the three mixtures together. Blend well; fry in hot fat at 360° like doughnuts.
When done on one side, should turn over.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into hot fat.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together to form balls.
Brown in hot fat. Place in baking dish and pour mixture of 1/2 cup catsup and 1/4 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
I prefer to drain fat from pan and pour 1 package gravy mix and water over meatballs.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Also good with mushrooms added to gravy.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Add sour milk with soda dissolved in it; add flour, then dissolve cocoa in boiling water and add to mixture.
Add flavoring.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350°.

title: banana pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon half of mixture into 2 pie shells.
Place sliced bananas over mixture, then spoon remainder over bananas.
Chill and then add fruit topping.

title: beef dip
directions: Beat ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Can be shaped into ball or put into a bowl.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: mashed potato cakes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then drop by large spoonfuls into hot oil in skillet.
Flatten each to form a cake shape.
Fry until crisp and brown on both sides, turning once.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil well; then add cake mix, Jell-O and wine. Blend.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread bean dip thinly over pizza pan.
Mash avocados.
Dice onions.
Mash one-half tomato.
Mix the 3 ingredients and spread over bean dip.
Mix 1 packet taco seasoning with sour cream. Spread over avocado mixture.
Cook and drain hamburger.
Mix meat with taco seasoning.
Sprinkle on top.
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top.
Dice other one-half of tomato and sprinkle on top.
Spread black olives on top.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Boil the butter, water, cocoa and shortening.
Add to flour mixture, then add eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Pour in glass pan and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate covered apples
directions: Wash and dry apples.
Insert popsicle stick into stem end of each apple.
Place on waxed paper lined tray.
Combine confectioners sugar, cocoa and oil in glass bowl; mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Microwave on High for 1 minute; mix well. Microwave for 15 to 30 seconds if necessary to melt.
Twirl apples in chocolate.
Tap sticks on side of bowl to remove excess. Return apples to tray.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Roll in vanilla chips, nuts, chopped candy pieces or drizzle with melted caramel.

title: carrots in wine
directions: Boil carrots until tender.
Drain.
Combine bouillon, wine, dill, onion, garlic salt and lemon juice.
Pour over carrots and simmer 20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; stir into carrot mixture.
Cook until slightly thickened.

title: spinach dip in bread bowl
directions: Defrost spinach and squeeze dry.
Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Fill hollowed out French bread.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops; place in casserole or pan.
Sprinkle rice over and around chops.
Mix soup and milk thoroughly.
Pour over chops and rice.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.
Uncover the last half hour.

title: homemade soda pop
directions: Stir together lemonade and four cans of carbonated water (three cans if using juice concentrate).
Gently stir until combined. Using a funnel, pour into 4-cup bottle or jar and seal.
Chill for up to 6 hours.
Makes 3 (about eight ounce) servings.

title: brownie frosting
directions: In a saucepan, combine the butter, cocoa and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring.
Mix in powdered sugar and vanilla until frosting is smooth.
Pour warm frosting over brownies as soon as you take them out of the oven.
Cool.

title: party macaroni salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix first 6 ingredients; add 7 chopped eggs (use eighth for garnish).
Add salt and pepper.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly spray 2 1/2-quart baking dish with cooking spray.
Place beef in baking dish, toss with gravy flavoring and flour.
Set aside.
Spray 1/2-inch skillet with nonstick cooking spray; set over medium high heat.

Add mushrooms, celery, onion and garlic; cook about 6 minutes, stirring occasionally until vegetables are tender but still crisp. Transfer vegetables to baking dish along with carrots, wine, beef broth, thyme, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Bake covered 1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovering to stir occasionally until beef is tender and vegetables are cooked.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 3-quart Pyrex or Corningware baking dish. Top with pieces of Swiss cheese. Combine soup and wine thoroughly; spoon over chicken. Be sure to cover between and around edges. Top with stuffing mix. Drizzle with melted margarine. Bake at 350° (uncovered) for 45 to 55 minutes (usually about 50 minutes, depending on individual oven and size of breasts).

title: chicken & dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken, save broth.
Remove chicken from bones and cut up.
Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Spread cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Mix package of stuffing mix, chopped onion, egg, evaporated milk, pepper together and sprinkle with Italian seasoning to taste.
Spread this over chicken and soup.
Pour saved chicken broth over all this until dish is full. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Check after 1/2 hour, if dish seems dry add more broth and continue to bake.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook
and brown sausage.
In
baking
dish,
layer
the browned sausage, sliced raw onions	and
Cheddar
cheese.
Mix and pour over the sausage
mixture,
Bisquick,	milk and eggs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in pie plate or baking dish.

title: cranberry sangria
directions: In a large pitcher or punch bowl, mix cranberry juice cocktail and peaches or nectarines, sliced lemon, ice cubes and club soda. Stir and serve.

title: sugar-free pear watermelon sherbet
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup skim milk.
Bring remaining 1/2 cup skim milk to a boil.
Pour gelatin milk mixture into boiling milk; stir to dissolve gelatin.
Add evaporated skim milk.
Chill until syrupy.
In food processor, combine remaining ingredients and milk mixture.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken. Pour into 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving time.
Serves 6, 77 calories.

title: chopped liver
directions: Cook the chopped onions in margarine until golden.
Add the chicken livers to the pan and cook, stirring occasionally, until completely cooked.
Cool.
Put in a food processor with the eggs and chop for 20 to 30 seconds.
The mixture should be a little chunky, but spreadable.

title: buttered, toasted, salted pecans
directions: Put butter into a large pan.
Melt.
Add pecans into a single layer.
Stir to coat with butter.
Bake at 225° until toasted. Stir every 15 minutes.
Add salt halfway through.
Usually takes about 1 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Do not cook pie shell.
Pour ingredients into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then lower to 350° for 30 minutes or until pies are brown.
Yields 2 pies.

title: jiffy pizza
directions: Spread pizza mix over hamburger buns.
Sprinkle cheese on top and toast in toaster oven until cheese melts.
A layer of pepperoni may be added prior to adding cheese, if desired.

title: german beef birds
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 6 pieces; place sausage on each roll.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Brown meat slowly in lard; drain.
Season with salt.
Add onion, tomato sauce, caraway seed and 1/2 the liquid from sauerkraut.
Cover tightly; cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add sauerkraut; continue to simmer for 30 minutes, until tender.
Serves 6.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin.
Dissolve completely.
Pour mixture slowly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill at least 3 hours.
To cut, dip bottom of pan in warm water for 15 seconds to loosen gelatin (or grease pan lightly and pour warm, not hot, liquid into pan for easy removal).
Cut shapes with cookie cutters all the way through gelatin, or cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Mix shortening, molasses, brown sugar and buttermilk.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Drop from teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
While still warm, frost.
(Butter frosting probably the best.)

title: summer fruit salad
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, in small bowl with mixer at low speed, beat cream cheese, milk, honey and almond extract until smooth, scraping bowl frequently with rubber spatula.
Pour dressing into small bowl.
Cut each nectarine into slices; discard pit.
Cut cantaloupe lengthwise into quarters; discard seeds; cut off rind.
Cut each cantaloupe quarter into wedges.
Rinse strawberries and blueberries under running cold water; pat dry with paper towels.
On chilled platter, arrange nectarine slices, cantaloupe wedges, strawberries, blueberries and cream cheese dressing in bowl.
Garnish salad with watercress sprigs.
Makes 6 salad or dessert servings.

title: mincemeat drop cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine in large mixer bowl shortening, margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Cream at #7 speed for 2 minutes.
Stop mixer add mincemeat, blend.
Then gradually add flour mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Beat on #4 speed 1 1/2 minutes.
Scrape bowl as necessary.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes at 375.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Toast nuts in 1/4 cup butter in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring frequently.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cream 1 cup of butter and gradually add sugar.
Cream well. Blend in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla and 1 1/3 cups of nuts.
Bake in three 9-inch layer cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and spread with Butter Pecan Frosting.

title: glorified cabbage casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper. Just heat through.
Do not brown.
Spread 3 cups coarsely shredded cabbage in a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with 3 more cups of cabbage.
Pour can of tomato soup or juice over the top and bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange bavarian
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water. Stir in sour cream until smooth. Mix in sherbet until melted. Chill until partially set. Fold in oranges. Pour into a 7-cup ring mold coated with nonstick cooking spray. Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight.

title: gooey snicker cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg, water and melted oleo.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Melt 4 regular size Snickers bars for 1 minute or less in microwave.
Add cream cheese and beaten eggs, gradually add 1 pound powdered sugar. Pour on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans; add green pepper, onion, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper. Chill.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Melt together butter or oleo and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: quickie clam chowder
directions: Mix together, heat and service. Serves 4.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until center of pie is set.

title: frozen caramel pie
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup water on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Cool 15 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup sour cream, then fold in whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker crust or chocolate crumb crust and freeze.

title: mocha fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans. Prepare, bake and cool cake following directions.

title: biscuit lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in water, tomato sauce, tomato paste, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Cover. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix pudding with pineapples.
Then mix remaining ingredients.

title: crab soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and bouillon cube, gradually stirring constantly with whisk to keep from becoming lumpy.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add crab just to heat through.

title: best banana cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.
Mash bananas, add to sugar mixture.
Mix the baking soda in with the sour cream and then add to batter, stir in flour.
Bake at 325° in a 9 x 13 pan or 3 layers of 8 inch pans, till toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool and top with cream cheese or butter cream frosting.
Delicious without any topping.

title: american chop suey
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburger meat, onion and celery. Drain excess fat. Add soy sauce, rice, both soups and water. Cook approximately 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add 3/4 cup chow mein noodles; mix well. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: herbed chicken superb(microwave)
directions: Combine
cracker crumbs, salt and paprika.
Dip chicken in oleo, coat with crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken, skin side up, in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave on	High
for
22 to 24 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Place large
pieces
to	outside
of
dish and small pieces to center of dish.

title: oatmeal rocks
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add eggs.
Mix the dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture along with the milk.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: beet salad by judy
directions: Drain beets and reserve juice (adding water to make 1 1/2 cups of liquid).
Heat juice to boil.
Add jello, stirring to dissolve. Add vinegar and salt.
Chill to partially set.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold until firm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans.
In a bowl stir together first 5 ingredients; set aside.
In a large bowl mix next 4 ingredients with mixer, at medium speed until well blended. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in carrots and nuts with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Fill and frost with 2 cups of whipped cream, if desired.

title: dodo's cole slaw
directions: Combine dressing ingredients and let stand before adding to cabbage.
Chill.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Put basil, parsley,
garlic
and
pine nuts in blender. Turn it on
and	gradually
add	olive oil.
Puree until fine. Add cheese, a touch of salt and grinding of black pepper; then blend briefly into a
thick
paste.
Cover in jar to use later or freeze in ice
tray.
The individual cubes can then be used later.

title: fish batter
directions: Combine flour, egg yolk, salt, oil and warm water. Fold in beaten egg white. Dip fish in batter and fry in hot oil.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion, egg and milk; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: noodle tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Add tuna, mushroom soup and onion; mix.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water together in heavy 4-quart saucepan. Cook mixture on medium heat, stirring frequently. Cook mixture to hard-crack stage or until the mixture forms wispy hair-like strands when dropped from spoon. This stage usually takes about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip orange cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add salt, rind and juice.
Cream well. Add eggs, flour and soda; beat well.
Fold in nuts and chips. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put a small piece of cloth over end of a glass and moisten with water. Flatten each cookie with this otherwise cookies will be thick instead of flat.
Bake at 375° for
7 to 9 minutes.

title: seafood okra gumbo
directions: Smother okra in oil for 15 minutes over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Add onion, garlic, bell pepper, tomato and seasoning. Cook for 30 minutes.
Add water.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and crab meat.
Cook another 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: shepherds pie
directions: In a large skillet brown ground chuck and onions; drain.
Mix soup mix into ground chuck mixture.
Layer mashed potatoes, ground chuck and cheese in a buttered casserole dish.
Repeat layers. Cover with foil and bake 35 - 40 minutes and 350 degrees.

title: diet zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, mix flours, baking powder, soda, and salt.
In separate bowl, combine egg, Butter Buds, sugar, Sweet & Low, vanilla and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients, mixing until moist.
Turn into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
May add 1/2 c. raisins or nuts if desired.

title: granny moore's spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add buttermilk,
then
dry
ingredients and vanilla.
Mix well and bake in
2 layers at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
After cake is cooled ice with Buttermilk Icing.

title: extra easy german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans (floured and greased). Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees. Cool and frost.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups of sugar, milk and butter.
Mix well and cook over moderate heat.
Take other 1/2 cup of sugar.
Put in skillet over low heat until sugar melts (stir constantly).
When melted, put into other boiling mixture and stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage (candy thermometer is nice to use).
Add vanilla.
Beat with mixer until a desired spreadable consistency is reached.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crumble crackers.
Add the rest of the ingredients.

title: mary's luscious rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion, celery and rice.
Saute until rice is lightly browned.
Add 4 cups chicken broth and 1 cup stewed tomatoes.
Cover skillet and simmer over low heat until rice is tender.
Add salt to taste.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Best to prepare dough a day ahead; better a week ahead.

title: farmer's market salad
directions: Mix sour cream and salad dressing mix. Refrigerate.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook slowly, stirring constantly until the mixture is very thick and has a nice deep reddish color.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: spicy cucumber and fruit salad
directions: With a melon baller, make 1 cup cantaloupe balls.
Place in a medium-size bowl.
Add the cucumber and strawberries; toss.
Stir in the lime juice, vegetable oil, chili peppers and coriander. Toss again.
Spoon the mixture onto salad plates and serve. Serves 4.
Preparation:
15 minutes.

title: healthy granola
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
To serve, place in bowl.
Can add sliced kiwi and strawberries on top of granola. Top with honey.
Put 2/3 cup yogurt for each bowl.
This is very good.
Keeps for a week in airtight container.
Can serve with milk.

title: kolache
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm and add yeast.
Stir well.
Add eggs and flour and mix to a smooth soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Make dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Flatten with 2 fingers to make an indentation in the middle.
On a greased cookie sheet, let rise until double. Reflatten in center and fill center with preserves.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and frost.
These are delicious hot or cold.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Combine in a large bowl with 1/2 cup butter, onions, sour cream, soup and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour in a 3-quart casserole.
Mix remaining butter and corn flakes; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice squash and onions into thin slices.
Chop peppers. Combine squash and onion.
Sprinkle with salt and set aside for 1 hour.
Drain off liquid.
Put vinegar, sugar, peppers, celery seed and mustard seed in pan and bring to a boil.
Add squash and onions.
Bring to a hard boil again.
Seal in sterile jars.

title: swiss steak
directions: Chop round
steak
into chunks and brown in heavy skillet. Chop onion	and
green
pepper
and add to skillet.
Add salt, pepper,
Worcestershire
sauce
and water; simmer until tender. Add water as needed.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar and egg.
Stir flour, baking powder together.
Add alternately milk.
Add blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 16 muffins.

title: hungry man's casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown hamburger and onion and drain off fat.
Stir in next four ingredients and heat until bubbly.
Pour into large casserole dish or cake pan.
Separate biscuits and lay out on top of the meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This is easy to double and take for potluck occasions.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Combine
cookies
and
margarine
(reserve
1/4 cup for topping).
Press mixture onto bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except blueberries.
Blend until smooth. Fold in berries with spoon.
Spray pan with nonstick spray or grease and flour pan.
Pour cake mixture into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour in a saucepan. Gradually stir in boiling water. Cook until mixture thickens; remove from heat. Beat egg yolks, lemon juice and rind together. Add to cooked ingredients.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, 4 to 5 minutes.
