Stir in butter. When slightly cooled, pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites, lemon juice and sugar until stiff.
Spread over lemon filling and brown in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Grease a
x	13-inch
pan
with margarine.
Layer of boiled and
cut
up chicken, salt and pepper.
Mix celery soup and broth and
pour over chicken.
Drain mixed vegetables and pour over
the mixture.
Cut
margarine
in pieces and lay on top.
Mix Bisquick
with
milk
and pour evenly over the top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and sift.
Working sugar in, cream shortening until airy light.
Break eggs separately into shortening.
Beat thoroughly each time.
Mash bananas with potato masher and stir into shortening.
Add vanilla.
Add flour mixture in several parts beating after each addition.
Empty into 8 x 4-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Slice when cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring 1/2 cup of water to boil.
Add sugar and Karo; stir until dissolved.
Cook to soft boil; add nuts and salt.
Cook to hard crack; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, soda, mace and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into greased pan; spread and flatten.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top of chicken breasts. Spread flat.
Lay chicken breasts over filling and fasten with toothpicks.
Coat chicken with flour and paprika mixture.
Brown chicken on all sides in butter.
Add water and bouillon cube. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
When chicken is done, with slotted spoon, arrange on warm platter.
Remove toothpicks.
Blend gradually heavy cream and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir into drippings in skillet.
Cook until thickens.
Serve with chicken and rice.

title: quick chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix with salt and pepper to taste and maybe onion and garlic powder added to a somewhat lumpy mixture.
Can be used on salad plates or quick sandwiches.
Serves four.

title: victorian nut bread
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans, or lightly spray pans.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Combine vegetables, chestnuts, onion, soup and mayonnaise.
Pour into baking dish.
Spread cheese over mixture, then add cracker crumbs. Melt butter and pour over crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate caramel delight cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Remove from oven; poke holes in cake with toothpick.
Pour Eagle cream over top and into holes. Refrigerate until cool, then pour caramel syrup on top and in holes.
Top off by spreading Cool Whip and sprinkle pecans on top.

title: stir-fry with ginger and soy
directions: Heat the oils in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add the ginger root and saute about 1 minute.
Add asparagus (broccoli can be substituted when asparagus is not in season).
Stir quickly, just until crisp-tender, about 2 minutes.
Stir in the soy sauce. Transfer to a serving platter and serve immediately or cover and refrigerate.

title: tostitos mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans on a tray with sides.
Mix 1/2 sour cream and salsa together and spread on top of beans (not carrying all the way to the edges).
Spread remaining sour cream on top of that (not carrying to the edge of underlying sour cream/salsa mixture). Sprinkle lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and jalapenos.
Dip with corn chips or Tostitos.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Cook with salt and onion in small amount of water until soft.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Layer and end with cheese.
Pour reserved liquid on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sally lunn
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in warm milk. Cream butter with sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Add flour and yeast/milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Let rise until double.
Beat well. Pour dough into a buttered Turk's head mold.
Allow to rise again.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: vineyard leg of lamb
directions: With the point of a sharp knife, cut a dozen or more 1-inch deep slits all over surface of the lamb.
Insert slivers of garlic into each slit.
Cut double thickness of cheesecloth large enough to entirely cover leg.
Drench it thoroughly with 1/2 cup brandy. Wrap leg in cloth and cover with plastic to prevent evaporation. Marinate at room temperature for at least three hours.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix cumin, salt and pepper in one bowl.
Combine sherry and wine in another.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve both packages of jello in the boiling water; set aside and let cool.
Mix milk, cottage cheese, pineapple, Miracle Whip and nuts in mixing bowl.
Add to cooled jello; chill until set.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add oil and celery seed.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with raw cut vegetables.

title: squash pie
directions: To cooked squash, add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat.
Mix cornstarch in enough milk to dissolve and add to preceding ingredients.
Add sugar and beat again.
Add coconut and stir.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils and remove any extraneous particles.
If using sausage, cut into small pieces and fry.
Drain.
Place lentils and sausage in 6-quart pot with water, chicken broth, pepperoni, onion, tomatoes, salt, oregano, sage and cayenne.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add carrots and celery; cover and simmer for another 40 minutes.

title: super supper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, blend potato flakes, sour cream and 1/2 cup water.
Pat firmly.
Brown ground beef and stir in remaining ingredients except cheese. Spoon over potato mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan with cooking spray.
Drain crushed pineapple, reserving juice. Sprinkle brown sugar onto bottom of pan.
Top with an even layer of crushed pineapple.
Slice cherries in half and arrange, cut side up, in pan.

title: ice cream supreme
directions: Mix crackers and melted oleo.
Reserve 1/2 cup.
Pack remainder in 13 x 9-inch pan and chill several hours.
Beat pudding, milk and ice cream and spread on chilled mixture; let set.
Spread top with Dream Whip and sprinkle reserved 1/2 cup cracker mixture on top.

title: the major's chicken
directions: Place rinsed and dried chicken on a baking pan, skin side up. Sprinkle half the garlic, salt and soy on the chicken.
Turn and sprinkle bone side with remaining ingredients.
Grill 20 minutes, bone side down, 20 minutes skin side down and another 15 minutes bone side down over low heat.
Serves 6.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Add pecans.
Spread approximately 1 tablespoon of mixture on each slice of ham and roll up from small end.
Place in refrigerator until very cold.
Slice into small rolls.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain. Add sauce and water; simmer 10 minutes. Cook macaroni. Spread 1/2 of the macaroni in casserole dish and top with 1/2 of sauce; repeat layers. Top with cheese and pepperoni; brown.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salad oil together.
Pour over remaining ingredients and marinate overnight.
(Contains 139 calories per 1/2 cup serving.)
Very tasty.

title: buttercream eggs
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; add vanilla.
In small amounts add powdered sugar until creamy.
Shape into balls or eggs. Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.

title: diet heaven
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding.
Add cheese and Cool Whip; mix well.
Although it's lo-cal, if you overindulge, the calories add up!

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and blend with electric mixer. Fold in chopped pecans and chopped apples.
Pour in tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix cake as instructed on box and pour the cake batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread rhubarb over the top of cake batter. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top of rhubarb; then pour cream on top of cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef with onions; drain.
Add rest of ingredients except rice and cheese.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add rice and simmer 45 minutes longer.
Serve with cheese.
Better second day.

title: italian spaghetti the lazy way
directions: Saute meat and onion until meat is no longer pink.
Leave meat chunky.
Drain off fat.
Add Chef Boyardee sauce, tomato paste and enough water for desired thickness (2 or 3 cups water), stirring constantly.
Season to taste with remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.

title: grape pie
directions: Pulp grapes.
Cook pulp until it can be put through a sieve. Add grape skins and sugar.
Heat; add cornstarch (dissolved in hot water).
Have crusts and hot oven ready.
Bake until crust is done.

title: health cookies
directions: Mix oil and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour with soda and salt, corn flakes and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Butter casserole.
Layer saltines (crushed), asparagus, boiled eggs (sliced), cheese and mushroom soup.
Put crushed crackers on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in greased casserole dish; add water and Lipton soup mix. Place chicken on top. Then pour cream of mushroom soup over it; bake 2 hours at 250°, covered. Check to make sure soup
is over chicken. May baste with soup if necessary.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Combine milk, eggs and seasonings.
Toss cheese with flour. Add cheese with spinach.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell at 350° for 1 hour.

title: limeade punch
directions: Combine lemonade and limeade together with water and add sherbet until creamy.
Then add seltzer and vodka to taste.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Then use spatula (not mixer). Blend in coconut and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy cherry crisp
directions: Put pie filling in pan.
Mix flour and butter; add sugars and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cherries.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine or butter, sugar, vanilla and brown sugar.
Stir in eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda and add to the sugar mixture.
Combine the cornflakes, pecans, oats, coconut and chocolate chips and stir into the sugar mixture.

title: hobgoblins
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients with fingers.
Shape into rolls about 1/4-inch thick and 6-inches long.
Arrange on ungreased baking sheets, curving slightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on baking sheet; remove carefully.
Frost bottoms with Ghostly Glaze, reserving 1/4 cup frosting.
Add cocoa to reserved frosting. Use in cake decorator with plain tube to make faces.
Makes about 20.

title: squash delight casserole
directions: Cook diced squash until tender.
Drain.
Add butter and mash. Add
other	ingredients.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with about 3 tablespoons melted margarine and put on and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: tuna pate
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add parsley, onion, flaked tuna, chili sauce and pepper sauce.
Add extra chili or pepper sauce as desired.
Chill 3 hours and serve with crackers.

title: cream cheese strawberry pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, strawberry juice and lemon juice. Mix until well blended, add strawberries and mix well. Then
fold in
Cool
Whip.
Spoon
over chocolate pie crumbs, chill overnight
or freeze.
Take out about 10 minutes before serving.

title: angel food cake with strawberries
directions: Bake
angel
food cake as directed on package and cool. Place on serving plate.
Cut a one inch layer from the top and set aside.
Cut around cake
1	inch from outer edge to 1 inch from bottom (making a ditch
in the center of the cake all the away around).
Remove cake from inside.	Set aside.
Mix jello with boiling water.
Put
strawberries
in
the hot jello mixture. Place cake center
pieces
in
jello.
Put	hot
jello, strawberry-cake
mixture
back
into
cake	ditch.	Place
the 1-inch layer from the top
of
cake
back on top of cake.
Top with Cool Whip and sliced strawberries.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together shortening and sugars until creamy.
Beat in egg, peanut butter, salt, soda and vanilla. Gradually add flour.
Use greater amount of flour if your peanut butter is heavy in oil.

title: terrific scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and add onions.
Simmer in very little water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine cheese and undiluted soup. Mix thoroughly, using blender, if possible.
Alternate layers of potatoes and cheese mixture in greased casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: clam stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms and pat dry.
Remove stems and chop (about 1 cup); set aside.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Use about 3 tablespoons of melted butter to brush on mushroom caps.
Place caps in a shallow pan.
To butter remaining in skillet, add garlic and reserved chopped mushroom stems; saute 2 minutes.
Add clams, bread crumbs, nuts, parsley, salt and pepper; mix well.
Spoon stuffing into mushroom caps, piling high.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes, or until hot.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain tuna and set aside.
Cook macaroni and cheese as directed. Add 1/4 cup extra milk.
Add 1 tablespoon extra butter or margarine.
Put in a casserole dish and add tuna. Mix well. Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° until crackers are brown.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool, then add other ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a large saucepan, mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Gradually add milk.
Beat the egg yolks and pour into mixture.
Cook over medium-high heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Stir constantly to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Stir until butter is melted.
Pour into pie crusts and top with meringue.
Makes two pies.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Simmer spareribs in enough water to cover, plus 2 teaspoons salt for 1/2 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients and cook over low heat for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain ribs and place in shallow baking pan.
Pour sauce over ribs and bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes or until tender, basting every 10 minutes with sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oven kahlua pork(this is the hawaiian pork traditionally roasted in the ground)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rub pork with liquid smoke and salt. Wrap pork with the foil, sealing completely.
Place in roasting pan and bake for 5 hours.
After baking, shred meat using 2 forks or fingers.
Excellent with rice and Aloha Sweet Potatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in apple and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipping cream or ice cream.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together.
Add garlic, oregano, tomatoes and paste; simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles for 10 to 15 minutes; drain.
Mix cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs, salt and pepper together.
Place alternating layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan or larger.
Begin with 1/2 of noodles on the bottom. Add 1/2 the cheese mixture, then 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and end with 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat all layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: marshmallow date roll
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup crumbs.
Combine remaining crumbs, marshmallows, dates and walnuts.
Moisten with cream and blend thoroughly.
Form into a roll 2 1/2 to 3 inches in diameter.
Roll in remaining crumbs.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill 8 hours or overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: plain cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in small bowl.
Cream together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add vanilla and milk; mix well.
Gradually add flour, stirring as you add.
Pour into 8-inch greased and floured baking pans.
Bake at 350° or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Top with your favorite icing.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, add white and brown sugars and cream well.
Add eggs and blend well.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add to mixture.
Sift flour and salt and add, then add vanilla and nutmeats.
Remove from mixer and add chocolate chips.
Chill dough before baking.
Drop a level No. 40 disher scoop or by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 360°.

title: strawberry soda cake
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Butter and flour a Bundt cake pan, then pour in the mixed ingredients. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans together.
Press into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown. Cool for 30 minutes.
Spread the softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and 8 ounces of the Cool Whip after it is all mixed together.
Spread the pudding on.
Apply the other 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
You may sprinkle more pecans on the top, if you wish.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Combine all ingredients and roll into balls, using 1 teaspoon mixture for each.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.
Serve hot.

title: grilled shrimp and sausages on red, red rice
directions: Place shrimp in a glass/ceramic bowl.
Add olive oil, basil and pepper.
Marinate 30 to 45 minutes.
Heat wine, prick sausages and poach 3 minutes.
Place sausages on grill; cook until done. Add shrimp; grill 2 1/2 minutes per side.
Place on Red, Red Rice. Serves 4.

title: make ahead breakfast
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Tear up bread and place in dish.
Brown and drain meat, then spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
May be assembled the night before.
Keep covered in the refrigerator until ready to bake.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: *Sauteed in butter or margarine.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown ground beef; drain. Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until veggies are tender, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings or 2 1/2 quarts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In saucepan, combine cranberries, water and sugar.
Cook until done.
Add salt and jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate until cool.
Add celery, apples and walnuts.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in mold to jell.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix together.
Drop by tablespoon about 1 inch apart on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately.

title: unstuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Brown hamburger with onion. Stir in rice. Place meat/rice mixture on cabbage. Mix tomato soup and water. Add bouillon and pour over mixture in baking dish. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: beef vegetable casserole
directions: Roll steak in flour.
Sear in hot grease on both sides. Place in baking dish.
Pour soup and 1 can of water over steak. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Good over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and Karo for 2 or 3 minutes.
Beat eggs lightly. Pour hot mix over eggs slowly.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans. Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: my pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding pecans last.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15
minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes or
until
set, when silver knife inserted comes out clean.

title: apple walnut supreme cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Combine apples and sugar; set aside.
In large bowl mix eggs, oil and vanilla; beat one minute at medium speed.
Add combined dry ingredients with apple mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes until cake tests done with a toothpick.
Do not underbake.
If desired, drizzle top of cooled cake with lemon glaze.

title: perfect meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients.
Shape into 1 or 2 loaves.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple-chicken salad pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pie shell.
Mix well.
Spoon into the pie shell.
Chill before serving.
Yields 6 servings. You may omit pie shell and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Combine the soup and soup mix.
Add the beef cubes, potatoes, carrots and onion.
Cook on low in crock-pot all day.
Stir once.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large container.
Serve with Good Seasons fat-free Italian salad dressing.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Prick crust and bake at 350° for a few minutes.
Mix all ingredients except egg whites and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° until pie barely moves when jiggled.
Beat egg whites until stiff, top pie with meringue and bake until brown.
(Total baking time for pie about 40 minutes.)

title: beef tips in wine sauce
directions: Mix and place in a covered dish.
Cook at 350° for 3 hours. Excellent over rice or egg noodles.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and flour; press in 8 x 8-inch pan and bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
While this is baking, beat eggs, salt and flour.
Add vanilla, nuts, coconut, brown sugar and baking powder; mix well.
Spread over first mixture and bake 15 minutes longer.
Cut in squares when cooled.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix well in blender for a smoother mixture.
Seal in an airtight container.
To serve, heat water or milk.
Place several heaping spoonfuls in cup, fill with hot liquid and mix well.

title: peruvian potato salad
directions: Mix onion, lemon juice, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the red pepper; cover and reserve.	Heat 1-inch salted water (1 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water), to boiling. Add potatoes.
Heat to boiling again. Reduce heat, cover and cook until tender for 20 - 25 minutes. Drain and cool.
Pare potatoes; cut into fourths.

Heat cream cheese, half and half, chilies, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and the turmeric over low heat. Stir frequently until mixture is smooth (about 10 - 12 minutes). Arrange potatoes on lettuce leaves. Spoon cream cheese over potatoes.
Drain onion, arrange on cheese and potatoes.
Garnish with olives and eggs.

title: rice-sour cream casserole
directions: Combine sour cream with green and red peppers. Season the rice with salt and pepper.
In a buttered shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange layers of rice, sour cream mixture and cheese (shredded), ending with rice as top layer.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese which is shredded.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mom's cucumber surprise salad
directions: Peel a good sized cucumber (enough for two or three).
Cut crosswise in middle, scoop out all seeds and let stand for a few minutes in vinegar diluted with water.

title: easy spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix with sour cream and soup mix. Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Blend next 3 and stir into tuna mixture.
Form 4 patties.
Fry in lightly oiled skillet over medium heat about 5 minutes or until browned.
Serve on buns (toasted) with lettuce and tomato.

title: quick deep dish chicken pie
directions: In saucepan, combine soup and the milk or cream.
Stir in chicken, potatoes, onions, pepper and seasonings.
Heat until sauce begins to simmer, stirring occasionally.
Empty into a 2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Top with biscuits.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 or 20 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: lemon herb chicken
directions: Place chicken breast halves between sheets of waxed paper and pound slightly with mallet.
Combine all dry ingredients, herbs, salt, pepper and 1/2 tablespoon of lemon zest with the flour. Dredge chicken breasts, one at a time, in flour.
Shake off excess.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken breasts without crowding; brown on each side about 4 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from skillet; drain all oil from skillet.
Add about 3 tablespoons of flour and brown.
Add chicken, broth and 1/2 tablespoon of zest, along with lemon juice. Simmer for 10 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mountain pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in pan.
Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Put batter over melted butter but do not mix.
In center put 1 can of any kind of fruit pie filling. Bake 25 minutes.

title: creamed green beans bohemian style(vamacka)
directions: Cover beans, onions, potatoes, salt and vinegar with water. Cook until tender, then drain off half the water.
Add 1 quart sour cream, dill and eggs and simmer about 5 minutes.
Stir so egg whites and yolks break up and mix with beans.
Simmer until eggs finish cooking or cooked fully.
Take out dill and serve.

title: chicken salad with dill
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Chunk or shred chicken.
Add water chestnuts, onion and dill weed.
Stir in sour cream and mayonnaise.
If it is not moist enough, add more mayonnaise. Light sour cream and mayonnaise may be substituted.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Slice bananas into crust.
Gradually add 1/2 cup milk to soften cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add pudding mix and remaining milk.
Beat slowly 1 minute.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: melon cooler
directions: Combine melon cubes, buttermilk or yogurt, honey, lemon juice and peel in blender and mix well.
Pour into chilled glass. Garnish with skewered melon.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: spaghetti meat loaf
directions: Prepare spaghetti and sauce as directed on package.
Combine spaghetti, 1 cup sauce and the Parmesan cheese.
Place in 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine meat, green pepper, mushrooms, egg, onion and seasonings; mix lightly.
Spread on spaghetti.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese in lattice design.
Cut into squares.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pie crust(one crust pie, 8 or 9-inch)
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Blend in Mazola oil thoroughly with fork. Sprinkle all of water over mixture; mix well.
Press dough firmly into ball with hands.
If too dry, add 1 to 2 tablespoons more Mazola oil.
Flatten ball slightly and roll into 12-inch circle between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Wipe table with damp cloth to keep from slipping.
Peel off top paper; place pastry in pie plate and prick well.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 450° oven.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in baking dish at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion and 4 tablespoons butter until tender; stir in flour and water mixture.
Add Cheez Whiz and heat until melted.
Place broccoli in large bowl; add cheese mixture; fold in eggs. Pour into buttered 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish; cover with bread crumbs; dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar well.
In separate bowl mix melted margarine, eggs, vanilla-butternut and milk.
Mix wet and dry ingredients.
Flour freezer paper and pat out dough.
Use cookie cutter.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cook about 20 minutes on floured pan.
Cool on towel.
Put in plastic bags.

title: no-crust cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat.
Add remaining ingredients; beat for 15 minutes with mixer. Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 1 hour.
Do not open oven door.
Turn oven off; leave cake in oven for an additional hour.
Refrigerate cake in pan for at least 10 hours.

title: lemon-herb chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; toss with chicken pieces. Brown chicken on both sides in butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until tender.

title: belly bombers(white castles)
directions: Brown meat. Drain. Add soups as they are, no seasonings.
Add cheese. Simmer until cheese melts.
Eat right away or put on buns and wrap in foil and freeze. Take out of freezer 15 minutes before putting in the oven.
Heat in oven 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes 24 small buns.
May take less time to heat in oven.

title: spinach and mushroom stuffing
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add onion and mushrooms. Saute for about 5 minutes. Add bread stuffing, cream, basil, poultry seasoning and spinach. Stir together lightly.
Let cool.
Stuff the bird.
Ingredients may be increased to accomodate a larger bird.

title: mixed berry pudding
directions: Combine sugar and fruit in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes, or just until fruit is tender.
Drain; reserve 1 cup liquid.
Line a 4 or 5-cup bowl with 3 bread slices, cutting and arranging slices to fit.
Drizzle 1/2 cup reserved liquid over sides and bottom of bread.
Let stand 2 minutes. Spoon fruit mixture into bowl.
Place 1 whole bread slice over fruit mixture.
Tear remaining bread slice into small pieces and arrange around whole bread slice.
Drizzle 1/4 cup liquid over bread.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Mix above; pat into a 9-inch pie pan.
Place in refrigerator while making the filling.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with cheese.
Mix soup and wine until smooth and spread over chicken. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix stuffing mix with butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours (a higher temperature will cause the stuffing to burn).
It's good to make ahead and let marinate.

title: hamburger roll-ups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Make biscuit dough (see Bisquick package). Roll out 1/4-inch thick into a rectangle, 18 x 8-inches.
Lightly brown onion in hot fat.
Stir in round steak and brown.
Mix in Bisquick, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly. Cook until thick.
Cool. Roll up dough like jelly roll, beginning with wide side. Seal ends. Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place cut side down on greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with Quick Mushroom Sauce.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease a small pan.
Place apples (peeled) in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Sprinkle mixture over apples. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together melted butter and cornbread.
Mix in cottage cheese, eggs and green chilies.
Fold in chopped broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift in flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix well, then add apples and pecans.
After mixing thoroughly, bake in oblong pan 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Butter a long casserole dish.
Place 2 cans tamales (remove shucks) in dish.
Pour 1 can chili (with or without beans) over tamales.
Cook in microwave 10 minutes on High.
Sprinkle onion over top.
Spread grated cheese over top of onion.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve over Fritos. Quick and easy.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix and cook first 6 ingredients over moderate heat until thickened.
Arrange layer of vanilla wafers; top with sliced banana in a deep dish.
Pour a layer of pudding over top.
Do another layer, saving some pudding for top.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together and set aside.
Cream the oleo, sugar, egg and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press down center of dough with thumb.
Drain cherries (reserving liquid).
Place a cherry in each cookie.
In small saucepan, melt chocolate pieces and condensed milk.
Stir in 4 teaspoons cherry juice.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon of chocolate mixture over each cherry, spreading to cover cherry.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Dice, fry and drain bacon.
Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients, but save some cheese to garnish top of casserole. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Sprinkle saved cheese around edges to form a border.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at least 30 minutes at 375°.
It's done when the center is firm, not runny.
Baking will take longer if the milk or spinach is cold.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together in a 6-quart pan.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer for 1/2 hour.
To serve, put crushed corn chips in soup bowl.
Place 1 teaspoon sour cream over chips.
Ladle soup in bowls next.
Top with some grated Cheddar cheese.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Chop peppers finely in blender, using 1/2 cup cider vinegar to moisten.
Put chopped peppers, rest of vinegar, salt, pepper flakes and chili powder in heavy saucepan with sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly for about 30 seconds.
Remove from heat. Add 1 bottle fruit pectin (I add a little more).
Return to rolling boil; skim off foam.
Stir constantly for 1 minute only. Pour into jars; cool and cover tightly.
Makes about 5 small jars.

title: taco casserole
directions: Combine ground beef or turkey, onion and garlic in a large skillet, cook until meat is browned.
Drain.
Combine meat mixture, tomato sauce, water and seasonings in a medium bowl; stir well.
Place half of meat mixture in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole; top with half of kidney beans and half of cheese. Sprinkle with half of crushed corn chips.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 5 minutes.
To serve, top casserole with shredded lettuce. Garnish with tomato wedges and sliced black olives, if desired.

title: dip for apples
directions: Combine all together and serve with apple slices.

title: hot dog roll-up
directions: Cut hot dogs in 3 or 4 pieces.
Cut bacon in 1/2.
Wrap bacon around hot dogs.
Secure with toothpick.
Place on baking sheet. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: nut pastry breakfast
directions: Slice toast into 2 thin slices.
Mix first 4 ingredients and spread on toast pieces.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and place under broiler until brown and bubbly.

title: christmas eggnog
directions: Mix together and serve.
Garnish with a sprinkle of nutmeg. Add 1/2 shot of brandy, if desired.
Enjoy.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: Mix together flour, powdered sugar, butter and crushed graham crackers.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely. Cream together cream cheese, Cool Whip, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cooled crust.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream together the cheese and sugars.
Fold in topping.
Slice cake twice.
Spread mixture between layers and on top.
Spoon blueberry pie filling over cake.

title: homemade v-8 juice
directions: Wash tomatoes; cut in fourths.
Chop the vegetables and put in large kettle; cook 30 minutes.
Put through sieve and add seasonings.
Chill and serve.
Makes 6 quarts.
Process in quart cans for 30 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil together for 1 minute the margarine, sugar, cocoa, milk and salt.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper; work quickly.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine beans, green pepper and onion.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over bean mixture.
Add 1/3 cup salad oil and a dash of garlic powder (optional).
Let set 48 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix ingredients with pineapple, add all other ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix together eggs, Mozzarella (save 1/2 for topping), Ricotta, cottage cheese, herbs and seasoning.
Add thawed spinach.
Spread some tomato sauce on bottom of lasagna pan.
Layer some noodles (uncooked), then cheese mixture.
Repeat, making tomato sauce top layer.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top.
Just before baking, pour 1/2 cup water (or more) around edges.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; sift flour, salt and baking powder 3 times.
Add small amounts of flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Beat egg whites until fluffy, but not dry, and fold in.
Grease three 9-inch layer cake pans lightly and line bottoms with waxed paper.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake springs back when tested.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and flour together gently.
Add milk, egg and salt.
Ladle into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes (until custard sets).

title: mae's best baked fish
directions: Mix.
Pour sauce over fish.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
A piece of fresh parsley is great.
Bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pig licking
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cake get cold.

title: macaroni pasta salad recipe
directions: Cook sugar and vinegar to a boil; let cool.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix all the remaining ingredients well.
Let set overnight.

title: brownie cake
directions: Make cake as directed on package.
In bowl, cream together the cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls and swirl around to make a marble effect.
Add 1/2 cup more chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: apple crisp ala laurel
directions: Butter a 9-inch cake pan or pie dish.
Slice apples and place in pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and water.
Combine sugar, oats and cinnamon.
In a small bowl cut butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy and delicious pound cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to	creamed mixture, alternately with the milk. Add flavorings and eggs.
Mix
well.
Bake
at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: kabseh(for 4 people)
directions: Add oil and margarine to pot; brown pieces of chicken on both sides.
Set aside chicken.
Toss onion in oil and margarine over heat until onion wilts.
Add tomato paste to onion.
Remove from heat; add chicken pieces, water to cover chicken, spices, cardamon and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Boil chicken for 30 minutes until done. Remove chicken; set aside.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Broil until broiler for 3 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Flatten crescent rolls onto bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread mustard evenly on bottom.
Cook margarine, onion, zucchini and seasonings.
Drain off about half of the liquid.
Mix together eggs and shredded cheese.
Add to that the zucchini, onion and liquid from pan.
Mix all together and pour into crust.
Bake about 30 to 40 minutes, until eggs are set.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, soda, milk, flour and cinnamon.
Add other ingredients (cut into small pieces).
Drop by teaspoons (not heaped) onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Saute sausage and onions until lightly brown.
Mix other ingredients together.
Add sausage and onion.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: four-layer dessert(serves 8 to 10)
directions: First Layer:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, chopped nuts and melted butter in a small bowl.
Mix together and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: oreo salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and pudding.
Add Oreos and Cool Whip.

title: caramel pudding
directions: Mix and boil first 3 ingredients.
Make a batter of rest.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Pour syrup over batter and bake at 350°.

title: smores
directions: You get a marshmellow and roast it.
Then you get the Hershey bar and put it on the graham cracker.
Get the marshmellow on the Hershey bar.
Put the other graham cracker on the marshmellow. Eat.

title: fast biscuit pizza
directions: Place biscuits on cookie sheet; flatten with glass.
Spread 1 tablespoon pizza sauce on each biscuit, then sprinkle cheese on each biscuit.
Put pepperoni on biscuit.
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer all ingredients starting with cake.
Let your last layer be Cool Whip.
May decorate with cherries and nuts if desired.

title: bojangles biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together. Blend in Crisco and buttermilk. Knead about 5 minutes. Roll 1 1/2-inches thick on floured surface. Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on greased baking pan. Brush with melted butter. Bake at 425° until brown. Remove from oven and brush with melted butter.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Squeeze through cookie press (any design) onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain
oranges	and
pineapple, mix with other ingredients. Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: emerald cantaloupe
directions: Prepare jello as directed, using 1/4 cup less water than indicated.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in drained pineapple. Arrange cantaloupe halves on a shallow tray.
Fill cavities with jello mixture.
Chill until set.

title: clam dip
directions: Allow cheese to come to room temperature in package.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Mix softened cheese with lemon juice, salt, Worcestershire sauce and clam liquid.
Stir in clams.
Chill well.
(Use reserved clam liquid 1 teaspoon at a time to thin if dip has become too thick.) Best served with king size Fritos.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix other ingredients together.
Pour over potatoes in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato or pumpkin casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients and pour into casserole pan. Then prepare topping.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix first 3 ingredients. Cook in ungreased 9 x 13 pan until slightly brown. Let cool. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 tub Cool Whip. Spread on crust. Fix chocolate pudding according to pie directions on box. Spread on top of Cool Whip mixture. Last, spread other tub of Cool Whip on top of pudding and sprinkle with pecans.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix and spread in an oblong pan.

title: mom's mustard pickles
directions: Fill jars 1/2 full with cukes and add remaining ingredients. This recipe is for pints.
(Double recipe for quarts.)

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix in order.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) graham cracker crusts.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine; mix with crushed Oreo cookies.
Press this into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze this, then put softened ice cream on cookie crust and freeze.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and refrigerate.
Add next 3 ingredients and then mix completely with broccoli, etc.

title: peachy blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Combine milk and melted margarine, then pour over dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish. Peel, slice and lightly sugar peaches.
(May substitute canned peaches.)
Spread peaches evenly over top of batter.
Sprinkle with blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cobbler is done when crust rises to top and browns.
Serve warm and with ice cream, if desired.

title: super simple cranberry sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine quick bread mix and butter; mix well.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls; place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Grate cheese and put aside.
In medium pan, fry the flour until golden brown, then add chili powder.
Mix a little bit, then start by adding 1 cup hot water.
Add more water if you need. Boil until it thickens.
Add salt to taste.
Heat in medium flame.

title: chicken with artichokes
directions: Cut cutlets into bite size pieces.
Shake in crumbs and brown in oil in frypan (medium heat).
Remove to baking pan (lasagna-type pan).
To oil, add fancy garlic and brown.
Add this mixture to chicken.
Cut artichoke hearts into quarters and add to chicken.
Sprinkle oregano, pepper and tarragon vinegar.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Line on ungreased 14-inch pizza pan with slices overlapping slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Spread mixture over crust. Arrange fruit over cream cheese layer.
Glaze with combined marmalade and water.
Chill.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: squash pickles
directions: Cover squash with salted water and let stand 1 hour; drain. Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard and celery seed in large saucepan. Bring to boil.
Add squash, peppers and onion.
Return to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Pack mixture in hot sterilized jars and seal according to canning directions.
Yields approximately 4 pints.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Add 2/3 of crumbs to mixture.
Mix thoroughly and form into long roll.
Roll into remaining crumbs to coat outside of roll. Chill.
Then cut into serving portions.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and molasses.
Mix well.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk to batter, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Bake in thin layers (about 1/4 inch of batter) in old fashioned black griddle (an iron skillet would probably do) for about 12 minutes in preheated 350 degree oven.
(These can be rolled out like cookie dough if you like.
Use a dinner plate and cut around it so the layers will be uniform in size.)

title: freezer slaw with onion
directions: Grate cabbage, sweet pepper and onion; mix and salt to taste. Mix vinegar, sugar and celery seed and stir over medium heat until mixture boils.
Pour over cabbage mixture and refrigerate.
Add turmeric for color, if desired.
When mixture is cooled, put in freezer cartons and freeze.

title: french lemon pie
directions: Grate lemon peel and meat; do not use the white part.
Mix all ingredients in order.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: no-mix cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk together.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour pie filling over mixture; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: banana-granola muffins
directions: Combine flour, 1/4 cup plus 3 tablespoons granola and next four ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine sour cream and next five ingredients; stir well. Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Divide batter evenly among 12 muffin cups coated with cooking spray; sprinkle remaining 1 tablespoon granola evenly over muffins.
Bake at 400° for 17 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan immediately.
Let cool on a wire rack. Yield: 1 dozen (serving size: 1 muffin).

title: flank steak with asparagus and mushrooms
directions: Slice the mushrooms and cut the asparagus in 1/2-inch diagonal slices to make 2 cups.
Place vegetables in a large, heavy frying pan that has a cover.
Add 1 cup water; cover and bring to boil, cooking over medium-high heat for about 5 minutes or until asparagus is barely tender.
Drain, reserving liquid, and place in uncovered bowl.
Add 1/2 cup water to the cornstarch gradually blending until smooth.
Mix in the red wine, salt, thyme, tarragon and garlic powder.
Cut flank steak in half lengthwise; slice each half on the diagonal into 1/2-inch strips.

Brown meat quickly in 2 to 3 tablespoons of very hot olive oil; reduce heat and return vegetable to pan with cornstarch mixture and cook for about 1 minute longer, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Blend in about 1/3 cup of the reserved vegetable liquid if you prefer a thinner sauce.
Serve with hot cooked brown rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef with onion and minced garlic; season with salt.
Warm tomato soup in saucepan or skillet large enough to soften tortillas in.
Add tortillas.
Put 3 tablespoons of meat mixture in each tortilla and roll up tightly. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour remaining soup over enchiladas and top with cheese.
Bake approximately 20 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: dawn's spanish rice
directions: Fry measured amount of rice you want in oil until brown.
Add onions (to your taste) and saute.
Add in small amount of tomato sauce and diced tomatoes and saute.
Reduce heat and simmer (covered) until very small amount of liquid is left.
Remove from heat and let sit covered for a few minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place shredded chicken in buttered casserole dish.
Blend the soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and pour over mixture.
Melt butter and pour over top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dressing
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter (saute).
Pour all in bowl. Mix and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix for about 10 seconds. Put in greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until it makes its own crust.

title: all american flag cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Remove from pan; cool completely.
Place cake on wire rack over sheet of waxed paper.
Poke cake using fork or end of wooden spoon at 1-inch intervals.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; slowly drizzle over cake.
Chill 1 hour.

title: homemade soap
directions: Dissolve lye in cold water.
Let cool.
Add lukewarm grease and stir until set.

title: baby wipes
directions: Mix in tub the water, baby bath and baby oil.
Cut roll of Bounty in half, place in tub (cut side down).
Put lid on and allow to sit overnight.
Pull core out of paper towels, dispense from middle.

title: bran oatmeal muffin mix
directions: Pour water over bran.
Set aside.
Cream sugar, shortening, eggs, buttermilk, salt and soda.
Add bran last.
Make in cupcake papers.
Fill half full. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Batter will keep for 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.
If baking from refrigerator, muffins may take 5 more minutes to be done.
Add raisins, nuts, mashed banana, dates or your choice of extras just before baking.

title: dan's own chops(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Crush Ritz crackers in blender or food processor and put in pie plate.
Mix in seasonings.
Dip chops in eggs and roll in cracker mixture.
Bake in oven for about 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and baking chocolate, broken into small pieces, in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Cook to the soft ball stage without stirring.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Stir just until blended.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields about 3 dozen pieces.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and mix into creamed mixture until just blended.
Stir chocolate chips and pecan pieces; drop by rounded tablespoonful 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Yields 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: refrigerator cucumber pickles(a delicious favorite year round)
directions: In large bowl, mix cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 1/2 hour. Drain well.
Stir in onions and green pepper.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and Crisco.
Work like mixing pie dough.
Add egg and apples.
Mix with fork.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° until apples are soft. (This mix is real dry.)

title: easy pecan rolls
directions: In a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan; stir together ice cream topping; butter.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Separate breadsticks but do not uncoil.
Arrange coils atop caramel mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes. Loosen sides and invert rolls onto a serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: beef burgundy over noodles
directions: Cube beef to 1-inch size.
Combine the soup and wine, mixing well, and pour over beef cubes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
If more liquid is needed, add a mixture of 50/50 wine and water.
Cook noodles in lightly salted water; rinse and drain.
Add butter and stir.
Serve in fondue dish.
Pour beef cubes and gravy easy over noodles.
Put a side dish of extra gravy by noodle dish.
Serves 100 people.

title: oreo parfait
directions: Pull Oreos apart and put icing in bottom of dish.
Any kind of pudding, make and pour 1/2 over icing.
Put in 1/2 tub Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Crumble up rest of cookies and put on top of Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: grannie allred's dill pickles
directions: Clean jars and cucumbers.
Pack in hot jars.
Add pickling spices and dill seed to each jar.
Pour vinegar solution over cucumbers and seal with hot lids.

title: moist and easy banana cake
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan or two loaf pans. Bake 40 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.
Test for doneness.

title: brownstone frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand for 1 hour.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and forms a soft ball in cold water (15 to 20 minutes).
Mix with mixer until just firm enough to spread.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place all ingredients but vanilla in top of double boiler in which the water is boiling.
Stir until smooth. Remove from stove; add vanilla and beat.
Quickly pour into 7 x 9-inch buttered pan. When cold, cut and remove from pan.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Blend soups and broth (part milk will work).
Stir in cheese; mix with spaghetti, turkey and mushrooms.
Turn into a greased 11 1/2 x 7 3/8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes until brown.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes and slice thin.
Put a third of potatoes in a shallow baking dish.
Add salt, pepper and cheese.
Repeat using rest of ingredients.
Bake about 30 minutes or until brown on top in a 350° preheated oven.

title: hot seafood spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Spread into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers or vegetables.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Stew squash and onion.
Add soup, rice, cheese and sour cream. Mix melted margarine and stuffing in bowl.
Line bottom of buttered casserole dish with 1/2 of stuffing.
Pour squash mixture on top and sprinkle the remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot horseradish dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, horseradish, pepper sauce and salt in small bowl.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes, uncovered.
Stir mixture after 30 seconds.
Sprinkle with chives and serve with fresh vegetables and sliced kielbasa.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix the corn flakes and melted margarine together and make crust.
Place cabbage, onion and cheese in layers over crust.
Mix mayonnaise and crushed corn flakes and spread over top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apple cider syrup waffle topping
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, combine first 5 ingredients. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils for 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in butter and apples. Makes about 2 cups.

title: homemade hot sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend in blender to desired consistency.

title: rose's banana split cake
directions: Melt and mix margarine (1 stick) and graham cracker crumbs together.
Pat firmly in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Mix eggs, sugar and remaining margarine.
Beat 15 minutes (with electric mixer).
Spread mixture over crumb crust.
Slice bananas lengthwise over sugar layer.
Spread the pineapple over bananas. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and top with cherry halves.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed.
In another skillet, brown ground beef, celery and peppers.
Add salt and pepper.
Add Rice-A-Roni and continue cooking.
Put into a casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: long island iced tea
directions: Mix rum, gin, vodka and Triple Sec separately in a pitcher. Add Lemix.
Add Pepsi to individual taste.
Fill glass with ice.

title: 20 minute pound cake
directions: Everything is put into a bowl at one time and beaten with an electric mixer for 20 minutes at moderate speed.
Put in ungreased tube pan and bake one hour or a little less at 350°.
(Important: Start cake in cold oven.)
When baked, let stand until cool before removing from pan.

title: good old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift dry ingredients and stir into mixture.
Divide into 3 or 4 parts.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
When dough is well chilled, roll thin on a lightly floured board.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on greased and floured cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly browned.
Decorate with icing or sprinkle sugar on cookies before baking.

title: surprise squash casserole
directions: Slice onions and squash. Cover with water. Stew until crisp. Not done. Add butter. Let cool for about 20 minutes.

title: italian sausage and spinach pie
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage and onion until brown (done).
In a large mixing bowl mix the following:
sausage, onion, spinach, cheese, Ricotta cheese, garlic, pepper and eggs until well blended.
Pour this into pie crust.
Top with other pie shell and flute.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix well until blended; chill.

title: low-fat tuna salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in boiling water.
In blender, combine Jell-O mixture, soup, mayonnaise, pickles and cottage cheese. Blend well and add tuna last.
Store covered in the refrigerator. Serve on lettuce with a slice of tomato for an attractive salad plate.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in molasses and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and ginger. Stir into molasses and sugar mixture.
Blend well.
Chill.
Roll out to 1/4-inch and cut into desired shapes.
Cool 5 minutes to firm before moving to rack.
Makes 2 dozen large cookies. Decorate with Fluffy Frosting.

title: fish casserole
directions: Place fish in baking dish. Mix soup with milk and pour on top of fish. Drain tiny shrimp and place on top of fish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered.

title: a cake for little bears
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions on box in a Bundt cake mold.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Drain oil from tuna into large pan.
Chop onion.
Cook onion in tuna oil until tender.
Add rest of ingredients, except tuna and rolls.
Cook slowly for about 20 minutes, stirring to keep from sticking.
Break tuna in large pieces into the sauce.
Cook 10 minutes longer, stirring as needed to prevent sticking.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: buttercrust pull-aparts
directions: In a large bowl or breadmaker, combine first five ingredients. If using a breadmaker, set bread setting on manual.
In a saucepan or microwave-proof bowl, heat buttermilk and butter just until warm (110° to 115°).
Add to flour mixture.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
By hand or breadmaker, mix in remaining to flour to form stiff dough.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and debone it.
Cook minute rice according to package directions.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add all soups and mix.
Put rice, chicken and soup mixture in a casserole dish and mix well.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Bake cake at 350° for 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put holes in top of cake with fork.
Pour glaze over it while cake is still warm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Press firmly into an ungreased 8-inch square baking pan or dish. Top with extra catsup and spread evenly.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake(no bake)
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine with crushed wafers.
Spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix eggs, sugar and remaining margarine together; beat until smooth (do not put in blender).
Spread mixture over crushed wafers.
Layer sliced bananas and pineapple. Cover with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts; garnish with cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to hot (450°).
Combine water, salt or spike and butter and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour all at once.
Stir vigorously until the mixture leaves the sides of the pan and forms a ball around the spoon.
Cool slightly.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat until the mixture is smooth and glossy after each addition.
Add the basil, prosciutto, cheese and pepper with the last egg.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until puffed and golden.
Cool on rack.
Store in airtight container and reheat in oven before serving.
You may substitute dill and smoked salmon for the basil and prosciutto for a different taste.
Try splitting the puffs and filling with a mixture of spinach, mushrooms, garlic and shallots sauteed in olive oil until moisture is absorbed.
Throw in a few toasted pine nuts for texture.

title: strawberry-rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and pineapple at least 20 to 25 minutes. Add dry jello.
Mix and pour into jars and seal.
Store in freezer.
Makes 4 or 5 pints.

title: nine day slaw
directions: Mix well and cover with 1 cup sugar.
Add liquid and refrigerate several hours before serving.
This keeps up to 9 days.

title: taco bean salad
directions: Chop and mix peppers, tomatoes and onions.
Add drained kidney beans and Cheddar cheese.
Toss and top with crumbled corn chips. Pour Catalina dressing on top and serve.

title: banana oatmeal chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all together. Drop by teaspoons on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Combine flour, sugars, soda, salt and spices in a large bowl; set aside. Combine buttermilk, oil, egg, egg whites and molasses.
Add flour to buttermilk mixture; do not overmix.
Pour into 12 muffin tins. Bake for 15 minutes, or until done.
Serve warm or cold.
Can be heated lightly; warm in microwave oven.
Very good.

title: stuffed beets supreme
directions: Cream cheese.
Mash and mix well.
Add sour cream and milk, grated onion, bell pepper and chopped pecans.
Scoop out center of beets and stuff beets with cream cheese mixture.

title: quick macaroni casserole
directions: Brown meat, drain and add sauce to simmer.
In large casserole, layer half the shells, half the sauce, half the sour cream and half the Provolone slices.
Repeat layers and top with Mozzarella.
Bake, covered, at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake another 15 minutes until cheese begins to brown. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, coconut, pecans and vanilla. Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Mix well; pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Whip the cream. Add to pies after they are cool.

title: simple spinach casserole
directions: Place spinach, cream cheese and onion soup mix in 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Mix well and pour in a greased casserole pan.

title: lemon lime pie(2 pies)
directions: Mix milk and instant pudding mix.
Beat on low until mixture thickens.
Add tub of Crystal Lite and mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer or in blender.
Chill overnight.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: strawberry-banana shake
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine all ingredients. Process until smooth. Makes 4 (8 ounce) servings.

title: sausage roll
directions: Brown sausage for 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook 15 minutes; drain.
Set aside.
Mix 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup with sausage.

title: carrie's 3 bean dish
directions: Lightly brown bacon and onion.
Remove from heat and drain. Stir in beans and all other ingredients.
Bake in shallow dish at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: ham and asparagus casserole
directions: Combine hot milk and cheese.
Blend 1/2 cup crumbs, fat, pimento, onion and parsley.
Add to milk mixture.
Blend in eggs. Cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook on low heat and slowly bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Simmer on low heat for about 10 to 20 minutes.
When cool, pour into jar and store in cool place.

title: butter thins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one by one, beating after each addition.
Add flour gradually and continue to beat until very smooth.
Pour into 2 dozen muffin tins lined with paper cups. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Pour fruit pie mix (aple, blueberry, cherry, etc.) in bottom of baking dish.
(Square or rectangular pans are better.) Sprinkle lemon juice over mix.
In large bowl combine cake mix, nuts and melted oleo or butter.
Mix well.
Sprinkle evenly over pie mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until golden brown on top.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli into florets and place in a large bowl.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and celery seed.
Mix all together and chill 5 or 6 hours.

title: helen's cherry walnut cake
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together.
Cream shortening and confectioners sugar.
Blend in vanilla and eggs (one at a time). Measure milk.
Add alternately with dry ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Fold in walnuts and cherries.
Pour into well-greased, lightly floured 10-inch tube pan.
Cut gently through batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.
While warm, spread top with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, shortening, spice, sugar, baking powder, milk and enough flour to make thick dough. Knead out in tray or pan, then make into biscuits and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° until golden and done.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Spread soft cream cheese in pan, top with chili over cream cheese.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Put in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve with taco chips.
Makes an approximately 10 x 5-inch pan.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Tenderize meat and cut in 3/4-inch strips.
Dredge with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot butter.
Add onions, mushrooms and garlic.
Combine sour cream, soup, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and green pepper.
Pour over meat.
Cover; cook on high heat, then reduce to simmer.
Serve over egg noodles.
Sprinkle with fresh grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cheese dip and chips(easy but good!)
directions: Cut cheese in squares.
Put cheese and chili in crock-pot and heat slowly.
Serve warm with chips.
Serves 4.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Melt oil, cocoa and butter in a saucepan; cool.
Beat eggs. Stir in sugar, then add chocolate mixture.
Fold in flour and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto heated waffle iron.
Bake for 90 seconds.
Lift out by edges with a fork.
Frost; sprinkle with nuts or candies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Rinse cans of soup with 1/2 water; add this to the casserole.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil
and
debone chicken and place in bottom of casserole dish
(save
broth).
Heat
soups
and
milk.
Pour over chicken. Mix
together stuffing mix with broth and margarine. Put mixture on top and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa and sugar.
Beat eggs; add them slowly. Add vanilla and flour.
Mix until smooth. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Grease a 7-inch iron skillet. In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour the batter into the iron skillet and bake for about 20 minutes. Remove from pan immediately. I like to
put a dinner knife (or some other utensil) underneath the bread to lift it off the plate slightly until ready to serve so that the bottom won't get soggy.

title: clara's fudge
directions: Combine butter, cream, sugar and salt.
Boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in marshmallows, chocolate morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir 1 minute or until melted.
Pour in foil-lined pan.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cut broccoli, cauliflower and onion in small pieces.
Add sunflower seeds and dressing (enough to coat salad ingredients).

title: squirrel with rice
directions: Dice salt pork; saute in large saucepan until brown.
Add squirrel pieces; brown lightly.
Add 2 quarts water; simmer until squirrels are tender, adding additional water, if needed.
Add rice, catsup, onion and seasonings; cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until rice is tender.

title: french creole gumbo
directions: Put oil in pot and let it get hot.
Cut okra in small circles; salt and pepper to taste.
Put into oil and fry, stirring often to keep from scorching.
Chop onion and garlic and add as soon as the okra begins to brown.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste and one quart of water.
After it is boiling, put in shrimp, crabs and ham.
Cover with lid and cook on very slow fire for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with boiled rice.

title: chicken and tortillas
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish, place 1/2 of the tortillas.
Cover with 1/2 of chicken and onion.
Repeat layers.

title: swedish doughnuts
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar.
Add the potatoes, buttermilk, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 1-2 hours on a floured surface, roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with a 1 1/2 inch doughnut cutter.
In an electric skillet or deep fat fryer, heat oil to 375°.
Fry doughnuts, a few at a time for 2 minutes on each side or until browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll in sugar if desired.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat Eagle Brand milk, eggs, sugar, vanilla and pudding mix with mixer.
Pour mixture into 6-quart ice cream freezer; fill rest of way with whole milk.
Follow freezer instructions to freeze.
My freezer takes 30 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and squeeze excess water from artichoke hearts.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or mini rye loaf.

title: sheet cake filled cookies
directions: Roll half of mixture on floured board.
Work dough to edge of pan.
Fill with canned fruit.
Roll remaining dough.
Place dough on top.
Close edges and press down in sides of pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes on bottom rack.
Then move to top rack at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: easy drop cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugars, eggs, peanut butter, water and vanilla. Mix flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add brown sugar and vanilla and beat again.
Dip pecan halves in egg whites and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 20 minutes.
Cut heat off and leave in oven for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool before placing in storage container.

title: roast potatoes with peppers and onions
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange potatoes and peppers alternately in spoke pattern in a large, shallow 12-inch round baking dish.
Pile the onions in center.
Scatter garlic on top. Drizzle with olive oil.
Sprinkle with rosemary, salt and pepper. Bake until veggies are lightly golden and tender, about 45 minutes.
Serves 4.
Contains 245 cal, 4 g protein, 11 g fat, 35 g carbohydrates, 700 mg salt and 0 mg cholesterol.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs 10 minutes. Soak boiled eggs in cold water for 15-20 minutes. Peel eggs and cut lengthwise. Take yolks and put into large bowl. Mix remaining ingredients well. Fill mixture into egg halves. Sprinkle paprika for a dash of color. Refrigerate until served.

title: party rye pizzas
directions: Brown meat with oregano
and
pepper
to
taste.
Drain well. Melt Velveeta and mix with	the meat.
Spread on slices of party rye.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on
top and add 1/2 stuffed olive. Place under broiler for a
few minutes until cheese is melted. Serve while hot.
These may be prepared ahead of time and frozen, then popped under the broiler.

title: chicken squares
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and set aside.
Take 1 (8 ounce) can crescent rolls and pinch 2 triangles together to make a square (pinch seams tightly).
Put about 1/2 cup of chicken mixture on each square.
Pull up corners and pinch seams together.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jello poke cake
directions: Place cake layers, top sides up, in 2 clean 9-inch cake pans. Pierce cake with a large wooden fork handle at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve each flavor of gelatin completely in 1 cup boiling water in separate bowls.
Carefully pour 1 flavor gelatin over 1 cake layer and 1 flavor gelatin over second layer.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Dip 1 cake pan in warm water 10 seconds; unmold onto serving plate.
Spread with about 1 cup Cool Whip.
Unmold the second cake layer; carefully place on first layer.
Frost top of cake with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Garnish as desired.

title: wieners in barbecue sauce
directions: Cut hot dogs crosswise in 3 pieces.
Cut each piece in half lengthwise to make 6 pieces.
Slit each piece through ends, leaving 1/4-inch joined in center.
Set aside.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Drain kidney beans and soak in vinegar for 1 hour. Drain all vegetables. Cook and drain macaroni. Add all together.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown ribs under broiler.
Brown onion in fat.
Mix ingredients together and pour over ribs and bake in cooking bag at 325° for 2 hours.

title: cheese tortillas
directions: Mix together.
Spread thin layer on tortilla shells.
Roll up and chill.
Slice and serve with salsa.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut, in blender and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Heat tomato soup, Jell-O, cream cheese and water until cream cheese is melted but not boiling.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Serve with veggies.
Makes a large quantity but can be frozen.

title: 3-layer chocolate dessert
directions: Mix oleo and flour for crust; press on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and fructose; beat in egg, water and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in sifter.
Sift dry ingredients into creamed mixture, stirring to blend thoroughly. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 30 cookies.
Exchange: 1 bread, 1/2 fruit and 1/2 fat.

title: taco beef dip
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Stir in water, beer, tomato paste and hot pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Stir in grated Cheddar.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 10 minutes. Freezes well.
Reheat in oven or microwave.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients.
Marinate overnight, turning occasionally. Bake with marinade about 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
When done, broil to desired crispness.

title: caramel morsel bars
directions: Melt caramels with water in saucepan over low heat.
Stir frequently until smooth.
Pour over cereal and peanuts.
Toss until well coated with greased fingers; press mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate and butterscotch chips over top.
Place in 200° oven for 4 to 5 minutes.
Spread softened morsels until blended to form frosting.
Cool, then cut into bars.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Clean chicken breasts and sprinkle salt over chicken. Cook until tender in water.
Keep liquid to use in stuffing mix.

In a casserole dish, put deboned chicken breasts. Add the mushroom soup over the breasts, then on top, add stuffing mix fixed according to the mix instructions, using liquid from cooking chicken breasts instead of water.
Place in oven at 325° and cook until mixture is hot.

title: orange-pecan coffee cake
directions: Combine milk, 1/4 cup sugar, shortening and salt in a small mixing bowl; stir until shortening melts.
Cool to lukewarm (105° to 115°).
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl. Stir in 1 teaspoon sugar; let stand 10 minutes.
