Add milk mixture, egg, orange rind and nutmeg; mix well.
Stir in enough flour to form a soft dough.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil together until it spins a good thread (about 5 to 8 minutes).
Pour over 5 quarts popped popcorn.
Form into balls.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions, except use milk instead of water.
Bake as usual.
While cake is hot, poke holes in it.
Pour over top of cake the following:
crushed pineapple and sugar that you have mixed and brought to a boil.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, milk and vanilla pudding.
Spread over top.
Layer with sliced bananas.
Follow with layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with cherries, pecans and coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: smoked venison
directions: Wash and trim venison of any fat or cartilage.
Make a paste of the other ingredients.
Make 1 inch deep slits in the meat 2 inches apart all over meat and stuff each slot with paste.

title: quick rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar, salt and oil until warm.
Remove from stove. Add the yeast.
Mix until yeast is dissolved. Add the flour. Mix. Roll out and cut.
Place in greased pan.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 325° until brown.
These are quick rolls that you can make up about 1 1/2 hours before you serve them.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add one egg at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add lemon juice and almond extract.
Sift in (fold in) flour.
Bake in paper lined stem pan at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chalupa dip
directions: Mix beans with taco sauce over medium heat.
Spread in bottom of serving dish that is 2 to 3-inches deep.
Mix picante sauce with mashed avocado; spread on bean mixture.
Add in layers the sour cream, olives, tomato, onion and finally cheese.
Serve with Doritos, Fritos or tostados.
You need a spoon to start, then chips.
Do not make more than 1 hour ahead and do not refrigerate.

title: fingerlings
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes, mushroom soup and consomme.
Shape into small log shapes and roll in corn flakes. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mushroom soup and consomme (or water) over top.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pork chop rice casserole
directions: Brown chops on both sides in drippings in a heavy skillet. Place in a 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Saute onion and celery in remaining drippings.
Blend soup with water; add to skillet with rice, mushrooms and seasonings.
Cook to boiling; pour over chops. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes longer.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured baking dish and bake for about 35 minutes at 325°. Makes 2 dozen.

title: sawdust salad(serves 10 to 12 people; 3 layer salad)
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in casserole dish with sides about 2 to 3 inches deep.
Let chill until firm.

title: hot pepper corn
directions: Melt the cream cheese, margarine and milk over low heat; add jalapeno peppers and salt.
Stir in corn.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, covered.

title: coq au vin
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together until sugar is dissolved.
Cool. Add the fruit juices.
Crush 5 bananas with a fork (or process in blender with some of the fruit juice mixture).
Mix the bananas with fruit juice mixture and freeze.
Remove from freezer one hour before serving time.
Mix 16 ounces of 7-Up to 1 quart punch. Serve slushy.

title: jewish crumb cake
directions: Prepare beforehand the 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and coconut.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients: flour, cocoa, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Add vanilla, mayonnaise and water to dry ingredients and mix.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350°.
Check with toothpick to make sure cake is done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk and bring to full boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in marshmallow and peanut butter.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat mixture until cooled down.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: harvest bake
directions: In iron pot (or flameproof casserole), saute onion in 1 tablespoon of oil until golden.
Mix all seasonings together. Layer vegetables sprinkled with seasonings; drizzle with remaining oil.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add sliced tomatoes; top with cheese and bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese is thoroughly melted and bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: sausage sizzlers
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef; drain off excess fat.
Dice cheese and stir into meat until melted.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Spread on rye bread and bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Season chops to taste and brown in small amount of fat on both sides. Pour fat off after browning.
On top of each chop, place 1 slice onion and pepper.
Place 1 tablespoon of rice on each.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over top of all chops.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; add milk to make doughy mixture.
Chill about 30 minutes.
Roll dough; cut in shapes.
Bake at 350° for about 9 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix salt, pepper and dressing.
Divide into 2 equal portions. Make batter of buttermilk, eggs and half the salt, pepper and dressing.
Mix remaining seasonings into flour.
Soak chicken in milk mixture.
Roll in flour until coated.
Fry in hot oil for about 20 minutes.

title: jamie's zesty meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly using only 1/2 of tomato sauce. Press in bread loaf pan.
Mix together the topping.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Mix together and bake according to directions on cake mix. Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch baking pans.

title: old time southern biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into a bowl (or use self-rising flour which has baking powder and salt in it).
Cut shortening into flour with a fork until you have pea sized balls. Stir in enough milk to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead gently.
(Try to handle your biscuit dough without touching it!
That's how gentle you need to be.)

title: noodles a la russe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, green onions and garlic in a skillet.
Drain fat and season meat with salt and pepper.
Mix together melted butter, sour cream, cheese and pimento.
Add meat and sour cream mixture to noodles; pour into a 2 qt. casserole and bake for 30-35 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Crush pretzels (not too fine).
Add melted butter or margarine and sugar.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir soup.
Blend in milk.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot top with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more until done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in a pan the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Cook on medium heat until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oats.
Stir well. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Eat.

title: janice's chicken cacciatore
directions: In large kettle, saute the onions, garlic and peppers in olive oil slowly.
Add carrots, tomatoes and salt.
Simmer.

title: turkey divan(for leftover turkey)
directions: Steam broccoli for 4 minutes; add rest of ingredients and top with cracker or bread crumbs.
Top with cheese and cook at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Cut chicken off bones; set aside.
Combine soups, broth, Ro-Tel and salt and pepper to taste.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer tortillas, cheese, onion, chicken and soup.
Makes 3 layers.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until hot throughout.

title: taco sauce
directions: In large pot put all ingredients and cook at high heat until it starts to boil, then turn down to medium low and cook until all vegetables are soft.
Add cornstarch dissolved in about 1 cup of cold water and stir into vegetables to thicken sauce, then put in sterilized jars.
Process 15 minutes in waterbath canner.

title: old bay deer steak
directions: Mix flour, onions and seasoning.
Tear a large piece of Reynolds wrap and spread butter on bottom and top. Sprinkle flour mixture on both sides of meat.
Using plenty of butter, wrap meat in foil, tearing more foil and wrapping the meat in the opposite direction.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°, turning every 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry-pineapple marmalade
directions: Combine pineapple, orange rind, pulp and sugar in a large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture boils and sugar dissolves; boil 15 minutes. Add strawberries and boil until thick, about 20 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently. Pour quickly into sterilized jars. Cover at once with metal lids and screw bands tight. Process jars in boiling water bath for 10 minutes. Yield: 3 pints.

title: sugar-free pineapple pie(low-fat dessert)
directions: Drain half of juice from pineapple.
Mix all ingredients.
Put inside crust.

title: gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan on top of stove.
Cook for 2 hours on low heat.
Pour over cooked rice or mashed potatoes. Very good.

title: spicy bourbon franks
directions: Combine
all ingredients except franks in Dutch oven or crock-pot.
Mix
well.
Bring
mixture to boil; stir in franks and heat 3, then simmer 20 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 15 to 20 appetizer servings.

title: trout stuffed with vegetables
directions: Sprinkle inside and out of the fish with spices and lemon juice.
Chop vegetables in a food processor and saute them in margarine until soft.
Stuff each fish with sauteed vegetables and wrap them loosely in foil.
Bake in oven at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in reserved beet liquid, vinegar and oleo.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add beets; heat through.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook ground beef in stew pot until brown; drain.
Stir in rest of ingredients and break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and cook, uncovered, 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Makes 3 layer cake or 1 (13 x 9-inch) square cake.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° (using 3 layers) or bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: pickled beets
directions: Select small, young beets; cook until tender.
Dip into cold water.
Peel off skins.
Make syrup of other ingredients.
Pour over beets and boil for 10 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: chocolate fudge cake pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine and chocolate in a double boiler.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together well.
Pour into a well buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook five minutes, until clear (cool).
Pour over strawberries in a baked crust, use whole or sliced berries.
Chill until set. Serve with whipped cream, Dream Whip or ice cream.

title: forgotten cookies(frances pritchett's recipe)
directions: While making cookies, preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Continue to beat while gradually adding sugar and add vanilla. Fold in chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil covered cookie sheets.
Put in oven and turn oven off.
Leave 8 to 10 hours. Do not open oven door during this time.

title: potato fritters
directions: Mix everything together until it's nice and gloppy.
Heat deep fry oil to 350°.
Drop the glop into the oil by tablespoons. As they fry, the globs of glop will turn into brown, crispy, delicious fritters.

title: mint chocolate chip ice cream
directions: Whip
cream.
In
large
bowl combine milk, extract and food coloring;
mix well.
Fold in cream and chips.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan; cover.
Freeze 6 hours.

title: beans and hominy
directions: Combine
all ingredients in crock-pot.	Cook for 6 to 8 hours. Serve with corn bread.
Enjoy.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix first three ingredients and pat into pan.
Mix eggs, sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Spread over crumb crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix pie filling with lemon juice.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Top with whipped cream (sweetened to taste).
Refrigerate about 8 hours.

title: kraut and carrot salad
directions: Mix well to blend flavors.

title: marinated seafood
directions: In a glass baking dish, place uncooked scallops; pour lime juice over them and let stand covered for 1 hour.

Stir in uncooked shrimp, chopped avocado (coarse), onion (fine), olive oil and coriander; refrigerate, covered for 8 hours or overnight. Spoon scallop-shrimp mixture into a dish that is then placed in a large bowl of crushed ice for serving.
Garnish with lime slices.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain
vegetables and mushrooms.
Place 1/2 ingredients in order
listed in a buttered casserole dish.
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cream filled angel cake
directions: Place cake on serving plate.
Slice a 1-inch layer from top of cake and set aside.
Cut around cake 1 inch from outer edge down to 1 inch from bottom.
Then cut around cake 1 inch from inner edge down to 1 inch from bottom.
Gently pull out cake from between cuts, leaving 1 inch on bottom.
Tear removed cake into pieces.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Use pastry blender to cut sour cream and shortening into dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 20 biscuits.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Mix beaten egg whites with Italian seasoning until mixed.
Add potatoes; stir until completely covered.
Spread potatoes on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with cooking
spray.
Bake at 350° until done, stirring occasionally.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter, milk and cocoa to a boil.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Spoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix brownie mix as directed.
Place parchment paper on a 15-inch baking stone.
Pour brownie mixture on the parchment paper and spread into a 14-inch circle.
Do not try without parchment paper because the batter will run while baking.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, or until set.
Cool.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend honey, salt, vinegar and mustard in pint jar.
Gradually add oil and blend.
Stir in minced onion and poppy seeds.
Chill overnight.
Great over spinach leaves.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cut sweet potatoes like French fries.
Put into greased casserole.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over potatoes. Pour unwhipped cream over potatoes.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: mexican bean soup
directions: Saute onions and bacon until tender.
Add beans, liquid and salsa.
Bring to a boil, cook for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.
(Other spices and herbs may be added to taste: basil, thyme, marjoram, bay leaves, etc.)

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: party punch
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
When ready to serve, place in the punch bowl and add the ice cream and sherbet.
Mix a little together and then add the Sprite.
Makes approximately 32 (6 ounce) servings.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Tabasco and onion may be omitted.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over bread cubes.
Combine the sugar, salt and beaten eggs.
Add to the milk and bread.
Then add the vanilla, butter and raisins.
Pour into a lightly greased pudding dish.
Set the dish in a shallow pan of hot water and bake in a 325° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: crystal's lasagna
directions: Cook green pepper and onion in small amount of oil until tender.
Brown ground beef.
Cook lasagna noodles until tender. Mix peppers, onions, drained ground beef and spaghetti sauce together.
Spray casserole dish with cooking spray and spoon out a small amount of sauce covering dish.
Then add layer of noodles, followed by a layer of sauce.
Cover in Mozzarella cheese.	Repeat process, adding in a layer of cottage cheese if desired.

title: black beans with peppers and rice
directions: Heat oil over medium heat.
Saute onions and peppers, about 7 minutes.
Add garlic and cumin; stir over low heat for 1 minute. Add tomatoes, beans, 1/4 cup liquid, salt and pepper.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Sprinkle rice into skillet. Cover and cook over low heat until hot.
Add more liquid, if mix is dry.
Add half the cilantro and mix gently.
Cover, let stand a couple minutes.
Add hot sauce to taste.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add oil, coffee and milk; mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Goes good with Favorite Icing.

title: diabetic coconut pie
directions: (This pie makes its own crust.)

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns.
Serves 8.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, sour cream, eggs and peach pie filling. Pour into ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, pineapple and pudding until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip and frost cake.
Refrigerate.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all together.
Pan fry. Drop from spoon.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Beat eggs, add slowly.
Add milk and vanilla; stir well.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage rolls
directions: To make dough, mix flour, fat and milk.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick on floured board.
Cover with sausage and roll up in a roll.
Chill thoroughly.
Slice 1 1/2-inch slices.
Bake in baking pan 15 or 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add syrup, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Stir in pecans.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell and bake 40 minutes in a preheated 300° oven.

title: triple strawberry trifle
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed with milk (2 cups) on package. Fold in 1 cup of the whipped topping. Cut cake into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart serving bowl and sprinkle with juice.
Spoon strawberries evenly on cake cubes.
Spoon pudding on, covering cake completely.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Top with remaining topping just prior to serving. Top with strawberry halves.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes approximately 5 1/2 cups.

title: s & s chili
directions: Saute the beef and onion. Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer for at least 30 minutes.
The super taste of this chili is the cumin!

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter; add 1 tablespoon butter with corn flakes.
Set aside.
Stir salt, pepper and flour with remaining butter; add milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add French fries.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use large casserole.

title: the best potato pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shells (2 large). Top with whipped egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain very, very well.
Add broccoli to "soup" mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish and sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple chunks in buttered dish.
Mix flour and sugar. Pour over pineapple. Sprinkle with cheese and cracker crumbs. Pour melted butter over this.
Bake at 350° for 25 to
30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Pour 1/2 box of cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in pie filling.
Lightly mix together.
Pour remaining half of cake mix on top.
Add butter pats all over top and sprinkle with pecans. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat together eggs, evaporated milk, sugar, salt, baking soda, flour and fruit cocktail.
Spray 12-cup Bundt pan with cooking spray.
Pour batter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes, then turn out onto serving tray. While cake is in the oven, make glaze.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain well.
Mix all together (except Velveeta) in crock-pot.
One hour before serving, add 1 pound of cubed Velveeta cheese.

title: italian turkey parmesan
directions: Mix first four ingredients thoroughly.
Shape meat mixture into large square about 3/4 inch thick.
Cut into 6 equal portions. Set temperature control of range at broil.
Arrange portions on rack 3 inches from heat source.
Broil on first side approximately 10 minutes or until done.
Turn portions over and spread with mixture of tomato paste and Parmesan cheese. Top each portion with a slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted and lightly brown.
Serves 4.

title: cabbage soup(lo-cal)
directions: Put all ingredients in a large soup pot with 8 cups water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 50 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple in casserole dish.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and flour. Sprinkle over pineapple.
Then pour pineapple juice over. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over.
Mix crackers and oleo.
Put on top. Bake 15 minutes in 325° oven.

title: mom's banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, bananas and baking mix. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Dump pie filling into pan.
Dump pineapple over pie filling.
Dump nuts over pineapple.
Dump cake mix over nuts.
Dump coconut over cake mix.
Dump melted oleo over coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: avocado tostados
directions: Warm tostado shells in the oven.
Meanwhile heat refried beans in a skillet over medium heat.
Layer each tostado shell with beans, guacamole, lettuce and cheese.
Top with taco sauce, sour cream and black olives.

title: cottage cheese squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Roll out dough and cut in squares.
Put favorite preserves in center. Pinch sides of dough to make hats.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until bottom turns slightly brown.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°; shake all in a plastic bag and place on roasting pan.
Bake for 40 minutes and turn occasionally.
Roast whole chicken, then place potatoes around chicken.

title: golden mushroom chicken
directions: Cut the beef into small pieces in bottom of pan. Salt the chicken and roll up in bacon slices.
Mix the soup and sour cream together and spread over the chicken.
Bake for 3 hours at 245°, uncovered.

title: chicken of normandy
directions: Combine bread stuffing and the margarine.
Add 1 cup of water. Place half of this mixture in a buttered cake pan (9 x 13-inch or 8 x 12-inch).
Mix the next 5 ingredients and place on top of stuffing and cover with the remaining stuffing.
Beat 2 eggs slightly with 1 1/2 cups of milk; pour over pan mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking and spread with 1 can of cream of mushroom, chicken or celery soup.
Bake, uncovered, approximately 40 minutes at 325°. Place slices of cheese over top and bake 10 more minutes.
Serve in squares.

title: fruit cake
directions: 1st Day:
Prepare fruits and raisins.
Soak in brandy overnight.	Add 1/2 cup flour to nuts.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter in fairly large saucepan, blend in flour and salt. Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly until thickens and bubbly (be careful not to burn it, easy to do).
Add potatoes, celery, carrots, onion and hot dogs.
Heat well.
Let it cook for a while.

title: currant bread
directions: Clean, wash and dry raisins and currants.
Sift flour.
Mix in sugar, lard, butter and then add spices and fruit.
Mix all together.
Mix yeast in 2 cups of warm water; stir into flour. Measure 2 quarts hot water and add 1/2 bottle Karo.
Stir and mix a little at a time.
Knead together.
Let rise until double its size, covered in a warm pan.

title: hard candy
directions: Cook to 300° with candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add flavoring (the more flavoring, the better the taste).
Pour on buttered cookie sheet; let cool.
Cut with scissors or break into pieces.
Coat with powdered sugar.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken with celery, grapes and almonds.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Fold into chicken mixture.
Refrigerate, covered.
Serve in lettuce cups, garnish with whole almonds or parsley.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix a syrup of sugar and boiling water. Add any flavor of gelatin to hot syrup.
Stir well until dissolved. Cool syrup.
Mix in lemonade, orange juice, pineapple juice, water and almond extract.
Freeze.
(Freezes well in five 1/2 gallon milk cartons.) Thaw at room temperature 3 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale before serving.
Punch should be slushy.
Serves 100.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Cut up cheese into small pieces.
Place into 2 x 10-inch dish with lid.
Melt cheese and sauce together with water.
Stir often. Microwave or stove top.
Serves 20.

title: cheese bars
directions: Mix
the cake mix, margarine and 2 eggs and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs
for 5 minutes and pour over the cake batter layer. Sprinkle with
pecans.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: fruit dip
directions: Add juice to dry ingredients.
Heat until hot, stirring constantly.
Add eggs to mixture slowly.
Beat cream cheese until soft.
Add hot mixture to cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Cut breasts in half and marinate overnight in covered dish in refrigerator.
Roll in bread crumbs and spread in roasting pan. Melt butter and shortening and spoon half over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spoon on rest of butter; mix and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: turkey chili
directions: In large heavy pot, brown turkey; drain off excess fat.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans, water, tomatoes, tomato paste, chili powder, oregano, cumin and red pepper.
Cover.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: monkey cake
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon in bag.
Cut 2 cans (each biscuit) in 2 sections.
Shake in sugar mixture.
Place in a greased Bundt pan.
Boil the margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Pour 1/2 mixture over biscuits.
Cut remaining 2 cans of biscuits, shaking in sugar mixture.
Use remainder of butter mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately. Invert pan on plate, being careful of hot sugar mixture.

title: christmas scent
directions: Simmer in open pan on stove during the holidays.
You home will small delightful.

title: cold tomato soup
directions: Into large bowl pour juice from the peeled tomatoes; chop tomatoes coarsely and return to juice.
Add tomato juice, salt, sugar, pepper, lemon juice and grated onion.
Beat with rotary beater.
Blend in sour cream and rest of items.
Chill for several hours.
Serve in chilled bowls.
Decorate with chives.
Yields 4 servings.

title: louise's oven baked stew
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Arrange in a large casserole.
Add other ingredients and cover securely.
Bake at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.
Do not remove cover from the stew for the first 3 hours.

title: twice baked potatoes(a little something different from a regular baked potato.)
directions: Wash potatoes and bake until done.
Can be cooked quickly in microwave.
Lay potatoes on side on plate.
Cut out top of potato and then scoop out potato, placing all removed into a bowl.
To potato pulp, add sour cream, cheese and salt.
Mash.
Return to potato shells.
Reheat in microwave 2 minutes.
Recipe can be easily adjusted for quantity desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in a skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain; add Ragu sauce mixing well and simmering. Combine cottage cheese, egg and Mozzarella cheese in a bowl, mixing until smooth.

title: divinity
directions: In a saucepan, mix brown sugar, water and vinegar.
At a low boil, cook until mixture is firm.
Beat egg white in a bowl, add hot mixture and beat until creamy.
Add walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into 8-inch greased pan.
When almost cool cut into small squares. Yields 16 to 20 pieces.

title: oriental joe
directions: Brown meat and onions in oil.
Add everything but water and cornstarch.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Thicken with blend of water and cornstarch.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, butter, syrup, vanilla and dash of salt, gradually beating each ingredient until blended. Pour into shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all together.
Allow the dough to set up in a greased pan for 1 hour.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: abe lincoln pie
directions: Mix sugar, milk and 4 egg yolks. Cook over low heat until thick. Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup warm water; add to other mixture. Add 2 tablespoons vanilla; set aside to cool. Beat egg whites and beat cream. Add both of these to cooked mixture. Put into crust quickly. Grate Hershey chocolate bar on top. Chill overnight. Makes 2 pies.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Parboil onions for 10 minutes; drain and cool.
Saute meat and chopped bacon in margarine; do not brown.
Add parsley, celery, milk and crumbs, plus 1/3 of stock.
Now, peel and scoop out centers of onions.
Stuff with meat mix and place in baking dish. Pour in rest of stock.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Baste occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Add sugar, oleo and flour to beaten eggs.
Beat well and stir in pineapple and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash
and
drain mushrooms;
take out stem of mushrooms (save for later use).
Cook ground beef and drain.
Add onions and
warm cheese;
mix
well.
Put beef mixture into mushroom "buttons". Place a toothpick in each mushroom.
Serve warm!

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until thoroughly blended.
Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake 14 to 16 minutes until browned.
Cool on rack.

title: italian chicken pasta
directions: In large saucepan on medium heat, melt oleo.
Stir in flour and let cook for 1 minute.
Add undrained stewed tomatoes, spaghetti sauce, onion, water and pepper.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add diced chicken and cooked pasta.
Let flavors blend for 5 to 7 minutes.
Place cheese slices on top.
Let melt and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cinnamon pudding cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, cold water and 2 tablespoons butter or margarine in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Set aside to cool.

title: ginger crackels
directions: Measure flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt into sifter. Sift twice.
Return to sifter.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually, creaming after each addition.
Beat in egg and molasses; sift dry ingredients over creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Form dough into balls about 1-inch diameter.
Roll top side in granulated sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven, 300°, for 12 to 15 minutes or until tops are slightly rounded, crackly and lightly browned.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: verlyn ketchers nacho potato soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine water, tomatoes, corn and dry potato mix; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, until potatoes are done.
Stir in chicken, cheese and olives; stir to melt the cheese.
Add milk until heated thoroughly.
Serve over tortilla chips.
Serves 6.

title: vanilla nut icebox cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together on a sheet of wax paper. Set aside. In a large mixing bowl, mix at medium speed. Mix butter until light. Gradually beat in sugar. Add egg and vanilla, beating until light and fluffy. At low speed, beat in half of the flour mixture. Mix in the rest of the flour mixture to form a stiff dough. Add nuts and mix well. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface. Divide dough into half with hands. Shape into a 7-inch long roll. Wrap in foil and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. Slice 1/8-inch thick and bake. Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Heat oven to 375°. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Add brown sugar to melted butter.
Add eggs and vanilla to mixture and blend well.
Gradually stir in sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread into 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and/or nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: homemade chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk. Cook until it comes to boiling point. Cook over medium heat for 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Break chocolate bars in pieces. Add chocolate bits, marshmallow cream and salt.
Put this in a large pan.
Pour half of the hot sugar and milk mixture into mixture, beating well and then rest of hot mixture.
Beat well. Add nuts and flavoring.
Pour into a buttered pan. Cool. Cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: saltine cracker crispies
directions: Bring the oleo and brown sugar to a boil; boil for 3 minutes. Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Lay layer of saltine crackers on foil, edges touching.
Drizzle syrup over crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; put the chocolate chips on top.
Return to oven just long enough to melt chocolate chips; remove from oven.
Spread melted chips evenly over baked crackers.
Top with the chopped nuts.
When cool, it will break apart in the size of crackers.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients well.
Cook ground meat until done; drain.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, chilies and dash of garlic salt. Simmer until most of the juice is gone.
Spread half of corn meal mixture in a well-greased pan.
Next, spread ground meat mixture, then the cheese, then the rest of corn meal mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Bring all ingredients, except apples, to a boil until thick. Add apples and mix well.
Remove from heat.
Put into hot jars with hot lids.
Process for 20 minutes (hot bath).
Makes approximately 10 quarts.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix pineapple, nuts and cherries with Eagle Brand milk.
Add lemon juice slowly.
Pour in the crust.
Let set for 15 minutes in refrigerator.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Cut and serve.

title: fiery cajun shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a bowl, mix all ingredients except the lemon slices and the shrimp.
Pour about a 1/2 cup of sauce into a large baking dish.
Arrange layers of shrimp and lemon slices until all are in bowl.
Leave about 1-inch of headroom. Pour remaining sauce over the shrimp and lemon slices.
Bake, uncovered, stirring once or twice, until all shrimp are cooked through, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with baguettes of hot French bread, a generous amount of napkins and bowls for shrimp shells.
Dip bread into the sauce.

title: frozen fruit candy
directions: Grind fruit and nuts in food chopper.
Moisten with orange juice and mix well.
Form into desired shapes and roll in coconut. Freeze.
The low concentration of sugar makes this candy especially good for children.
Keep in bag in freezer for snacks.

title: chocolate cake roll
directions: Note:
Any cake mix or ice cream if okay.

title: lucille's jelly roll
directions: Whip eggs until very, very fluffy, then mix sugar in very slowly and flour.
Add vanilla, baking soda and salt.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes.
Cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and peppers in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in bag, coating potatoes well with cheese mixture.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Mix flour, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper together.
Put into plastic bag.
Moisten potato pieces.
Place two at a time in bag and shake to coat.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place coated potato pieces in single layer and bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once, until potatoes are golden brown.

title: banana orange muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Blend orange juice, bananas and eggs.
Stir in flour mixture, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes in muffin tins.

title: corn bread cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: green onion dip
directions: In blender or food processor, blend all ingredients until almost smooth.
Cover; chill.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Good with chicken or ham and also makes an excellent winter dessert.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Place ingredients in crock-pot and cook on high for 30 minutes. Serve with toothpicks.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crumble crackers and mix with melted butter, set aside one cup of crackers.
Soften ice cream until creamy and add milk and pudding mix.
Line bottom of 9x13 inch pan with crackers.
Top with coconut cream mix.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Top with cool whip and cracker crumbs.

title: tomato surprise salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot puree.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend, electric mixer on high.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch mold.
Chill at least 4 hours, overnight if possible.
Cut into 4-inch squares.
Serve over leaf lettuce.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: swiss cheese and veggie soup
directions: In
a medium saucepan combine frozen vegetables, onion, water and
bouillon; bring to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer
about
10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Transfer all of the vegetables and cooking liquid to a blender or food processor; add milk.
Cover and blend or process until smooth. Return
mixture to saucepan and stir in cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
(Test with knife for doneness.)
Freezes well.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Cut everything except cherries to bite size. Add sugar and salt. Chill and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except shrimp) with mixer.
Add shrimp and mix again.
Double recipe for parties or get togethers.

title: punch
directions: Mix together bananas, sugar and water.
Mix and add lemonade and juices.
Add diet Sprite and serve over crushed ice.

title: shrimp acapulco
directions: Simmer shrimp in butter for 3 minutes, until pink, turning them often.
Add garlic, onions and chives.
Pour in brandy and wine.
Squeeze juice of 1 small lemon over all.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve with chunks of French bread to dip in sauce.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: crab-shrimp ball
directions: Wash shrimp and crab, taking care to remove shell pieces from crab.
Drain and pat dry.
Blend cream cheese, horseradish and lemon juice with mixer.
Stir in crab and shrimp.
Shape into ball.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill.
Pour cocktail over top when ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown stew meat with onion in large pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Serve over noodles or potatoes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In large skillet, place chicken breast that is boneless, skinless and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Add oil.
Cook, over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned (about 3 minutes).
Add stir-fry vegetable mix and garlic.
Cook, stirring frequently, 2 minutes longer.

title: croutons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter with oil and garlic cloves. Salt and pepper to taste over low heat.
Remove from heat; let stand for 10 minutes.
Discard garlic.
Cut bread slices into 3/4-inch squares.
In a bowl, toss butter mixture with bread squares.
Spread bread out over baking sheet pan.
Bake for 12 minutes or until golden.
Let cool and serve.

title: potato chip cookies(makes 100 cookies)
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Add flour, baking soda and vanilla; mix well.
Add nuts and crushed potato chips.
Dip with a #16 scoop.
Press down with a flat object. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine honey, oil and eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in honey mixture.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake in 3 greased 8-inch round cake pans at 325° for 45 minutes.
Spread with cream cheese frosting.

title: greek salata
directions: Tear the lettuce into bite size pieces. Toss with cucumber, radishes and onions.
Arrange lettuce, vegetables and tomatoes in salad bowl. Garnish with olives, cheese and anchovies; refrigerate.
Shake remaining ingredients in tightly covered jar; refrigerate.
Shake dressing and pour over salad. Toss to serve.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Have everything ready before starting mixing.
Mix milk and cherry juice, add crumbs, stir; add
nuts and marshmallows and mix with your hands.
When mixed good put out on aluminum foil with powdered sugar on it.
Shape into a loaf, roll
foil around it, and put into refrigerator.
It is better if you leave it for several hours or overnight.
It will keep for a long time.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix water, margarine, flavoring and cake mix in large mixing bowl.
Mix for 1 minute.
Then add eggs and beat on medium speed for 2 more minutes.
Pour into a tube cake pan that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, turn out of pan and leave it bottom side up.
When cool, ice it with Lemon Icing recipe.

title: jennifer's tony tiger cereal cookies
directions: Mix in big bowl.
Put in pan.
Bake in oven.
Decorate with hearts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients to moisten well.
Fold into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until nicely browned.

title: butter gooey coffee cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, 1 stick butter and 2 eggs.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the 4x sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs and the vanilla flavoring.
Spread over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: butter stars
directions: Sift flour on board.
Add sugar.
Cut in butter with knife until crumbly.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
(This takes quite a while.)
Beat 2 egg whites a little; brush on cookies and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Stir in molasses and beaten eggs. Re-sift flour and other dry ingredients.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat batter after each addition until blended.
Bake in greased 9-inch tube pan in moderate oven (350°) about 45 minutes.
Serve warm with raisin sauce.
May be cooled and iced.

title: aunt boe's coconut balls
directions: Melt butter slowly and add milk.
Stir in sugar and salt; add coconut and pecans.
Chill until easily handled and roll into balls.
Melt chocolate pieces and paraffin together in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat and dip each ball, removing candy quickly from chocolate mixture and placing on waxed paper.
Take a small number of balls out of refrigerator at a time to prevent them from getting soft.
Store in air tight container.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer sauce for 1 hour. Brown your meat.

title: butterscotch chocolate squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening; stir in sugar.
Cool.
Beat eggs, flour, nuts and chocolate.
Pour in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spareribs with sauerkraut
directions: Split ribs (every other) and wash.
Salt and pepper ribs. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn.
Bake 15 minutes more until brown.
Rinse sauerkraut with cold water.
In large pan, layer with cabbage, carrots, onion, sauerkraut and apple.
Add ribs. Make a second layer, ending with sauerkraut.
Add water to cover. Bring to a first boil, then simmer for 1 1/2 hours until sauerkraut is transparent.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat 1 cup of water to a rolling boil in saucepan and add Crisco butter.
Stir in flour, all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture leaves the pan and forms into a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in thoroughly one at a time the 4 eggs.
Beat mixture until smooth and velvety.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until dry.
Allow to cool.
Cut off top with sharp knife.
Scoop out any filaments of soft dough, then chill.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package; drain well. Place in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice, stirring well.
Spoon mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lazy squash
directions: Combine onion and squash.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add beaten egg and milk.
Put half of squash mixture in casserole. Sprinkle half of crumbs and half of cheese over.
Add rest of squash mixture, rest of crumbs and rest of cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna hot dish
directions: Cook macaroni in salted, boiling water.
Drain and combine with the remaining ingredients.
Everything except noodles and tuna can be whizzed in the blender.
Place in buttered baking dish (2-quart) and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato and leek chowder
directions: Melt butter; add leeks, potatoes, carrots and onion.
Cook slowly until soft, stirring often.
Add chicken broth; cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 25 minutes.

title: colonial beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon in a 1-quart casserole. Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs, one at a time. Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to creamed mixture alternately with flour, reserving 1 cup flour.	Stir mixture after each addition;
add flavoring.
Stir reserved
flour
over
chopped fruits, candy and nuts.
Mix well;	fold
into
cake
mixture. Place in floured and greased tube pan;
bake
at
for
3 hours.
Mix orange juice and sugar;
pour
over hot cake while it is still in pan.
Cool cake thoroughly before removing from pan.

title: romaine, red onion and orange salad
directions: Soak onion in ice water for 10 minutes. Drain.
In a small bowl or jar, whisk orange juice, oil, mustard, parsley, garlic, sugar, salt and pepper.
Put lettuce on platter.
Arrange orange slices and then onion on top. Drizzle dressing over and toss. Serves 4.

title: cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cream shortening.
Add sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well and then add dry ingredients.
Nuts, raisins or chocolate chips may be added.
Place on cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake until light brown in low temperature oven.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, oil and vinegar.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Add milk slowly. Add flavoring and food coloring.
Bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees. Makes 3 layers or 1 sheet cake.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Combine eggs, corn syrup, vanilla, sugar and melted margarine.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut cake(chocolate)
directions: Rinse sauerkraut.
Snip or chop into small pieces.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Blend vanilla with sugar and butter.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with water.
Fold in sauerkraut.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered and floured pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: johnny mathis' wild duck
directions: Clean ducks; rub with salt and pepper.
Place in baking pan, breast side up.
Add onion, green pepper, celery and water to pan; cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until ducks are tender, basting occasionally.
Serve on a bed of wild rice.

title: easy coconut cream pie
directions: Mix 1 cup milk, Dream whip and vanilla with hand mixer until stiff (or peaks).
Add 1 cup milk and the pudding and mix well. Add coconut.
Pour into crust and top with Cool Whip.
You can also brown coconut to add to the top of the Cool Whip if desired.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in water until tender.
Drain.
Saute bacon until crisp.
Reserving 2 Tbsp drippings, then discard remainder of drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Saute onion and celery in bacon drippings.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese, and simmer.
You may add cornstarch to thicken.
Garnish with cheese.

title: anita's easy bake potatoes
directions: Pam spray a pyrex baking dish.
Add potatoes, dot around with butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with Zesty Italian dry salad dressing mix; add the water and cover with foil.
Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
(Remove foil and stir well a couple of times during baking; replace foil and continue baking.)
Remove foil and bake until potatoes brown a little.

title: blackening spice
directions: Combine thoroughly.
Use cast-iron skillet, heat until gray ash forms on high 10 to 20 minutes.
Drizzle butter as cooking. Sprinkle spice on desired meat (fish, chicken, beef).

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix butter and crumbs and put in 9-inch pan.
Place coconut, morsels and nuts in crust in order given.
Pour condensed milk over all and smooth evenly.

title: strawberry cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients except strawberry preserves.
Mold into a ring; chill in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, fill center with preserves.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Mix together all fruit, coconut and nuts. Add the 2 cans condensed milk and let sit about 2 hours or so until it absorbs the milk. Press firmly into 2 loaf pans that have been greased and lined with heavy waxed paper. Bake for 1 hour at 300°. (Keeps well in the freezer.) I use 2 long slender loaf pans.

title: baked italian peas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place peas in colander and rinse under cool water, thaw and drain.
In a large bowl, combine peas with remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add the corn bread mix last. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 12 squares.

title: plantation pralines
directions: Line 2 large cookie sheets with waxed paper.
In a large saucepan, combine sugar, brown sugar and cream.
Cook over medium heat until boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in pecans and cook until mixture reaches the soft ball stage (235° to 240°).
Remove from heat; add butter and salt.
Stir vigorously until mixture starts to thicken and becomes cloudy.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together. Sift dry ingredients together and add shortening mixture, blending well. Chill dough. Shape into balls the size of a walnut and roll in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place 2-inches apart on a greased baking sheet. Bake until brown, but soft in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out with crinkley tops.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels over low heat (double boiler); add noodles and peanuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set until hardened.

title: mayonnaise cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork until thoroughly mixed.
Make balls, use teaspoon.
Mash with a floured fork.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes.

title: coffee can pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs at low speed. Add pumpkin, water and dry ingredients. Add nuts. Place batter in 4 greased and floured 1-pound coffee cans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. This freezes well.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces.
Place a layer of angel food cake, followed by a layer of cherries, and top it off with a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat this sequence to the top of the bowl.
(Should have at least 3 layers of each ingredient.) Decorate the middle of the top with candy or cherries.
(You can substitute the cherries with strawberries when in season.)
Chill and serve.

title: tri-color jello
directions: Stir 4 envelopes of Knox gelatine and the sweetened condensed milk with 4 cups of boiling water.
Pour 1/4 of the mixture slowly into an adequate size pan.
Chill for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down biscuits(yields 10 biscuits)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir the Cheddar into the dry ingredients until all the particles of cheese are coated with flour. Beat the egg with the milk and stir this into the flour mixture until just blended, then add the butter. Bake the batter in greased muffin tins for 20 minutes.

title: nora jean's punch
directions: Put in 3 gallon bags and freeze.
Defrost until barely crunchy.
Add 1 to 2 liters pop (ginger ale or lemon lime or 7-Up) to each bag.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta according to box and rinse in cold water.
Heat sauce to which you have added seasonings to taste: 1/2 cup water, garlic powder, salt, basil, oregano or crushed red pepper seed, cheese and sugar.
Combine all ingredients, except sauce mixture and 1/4 to 1/2 cup cheese, and stuff each shell with one tablespoon or so of filling.
Cover bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with sauce, then place the filled shells in a single layer in pan. Cover with remaining sauce, then sprinkle with remaining grated cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes approximately 7 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon and crumble; set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Then add broccoli, cheese and bacon.
Let stand overnight.

title: miniature white fruit cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift 1 1/2 cups flour, salt and baking powder; add alternately with pineapple juice to first mixture. Dust fruit with 1/2 cup flour.
Add fruit, coconut and nuts to mixture.
Mix only until well blended.

title: caramel ring
directions: In a large Bundt pan (do not grease), sprinkle bottom with nuts and the package of butterscotch pudding.
Place the frozen dinner rolls over the nuts and pudding.
Melt butter, sugar and cinnamon in small pan; spoon over rolls.
Let stand overnight, uncovered.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let set 5 minutes; turn out.

title: mamaw borders' freezer jam
directions: Mix berries and sugar.
Let stand for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Mix water and Sure-Jell; bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Stir in strawberries and keep stirring for 2 minutes more. This jells very fast, so pour into containers quickly!!
Once cooled to room temperature, freeze.

title: company chicken
directions: Combine melted margarine and cracker crumbs.
Spoon half of crumbs in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with chicken.
Combine sour cream, soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken. Top with remaining crumbs and cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Layer in crock-pot as listed (do not stir until cooked): stew meat, dry onion soup or onion, baby carrots, potatoes, frozen peas, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and tomato soup. Cook on low for the day (approximately 6 to 8 hours).
Stir and enjoy.

title: italian beef
directions: Roast meat, uncovered, about 2 1/2 hours.
Cool and slice. Add water to pan drippings; stir in other ingredients.
Add beef and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Reheat to serve.
Remove beef from marinade before serving.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Slowly add flour, salt, milk and flavorings with mixer on low.
Turn mixer to medium; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: grandma's baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add tomato juice and cheese alternately.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in large bowl or glass container in the refrigerator and cover tightly.
Use as needed.
(Will keep approximately 2 weeks, if it has a chance.)
No need to let rise before baking.
Bake in a moderate oven.

title: crab and shrimp salad
directions: Mix
and
let set overnight or all day.
Add 1 pound of crab or	shrimp.
(Or
you
may use 2 small cans of each.) You may freeze.
Use as salad or spread on small rye buffet bread.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Combine gelatin and 1 cup boiling water, stirring 2 minutes or until gelatin dissolves.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in yogurt and whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until firm. Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
In a large mixing bowl, cream together margarine, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, cloves, sugar and egg until well blended.
Gradually mix in pumpkin, sifted ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonful about 1-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake about 15 minutes or until just beginning to brown at edge.
Remove cookies to rack and cool.
Frost tops with white or maple frosting.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put in large kettle juice, onions and peppers.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook for 1 hour.
Fill jars and seal. Makes 11 to 12 quarts.

title: sponge upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cover butter with brown sugar. Lay pineapple in form of skillet.
Put cherries in the center of pineapple.
Beat
egg
yolks;
add
flour, sugar and fruit juice and
stir.
Beat the whites of 3 eggs until formed; add to
mix. Pour
over
fruit.
Bake
minutes at 350°.
When done, flip over on plate.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes.
Grate onion; put in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, milk and melted butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper and mix.
Pour the batter from a 1/4 cup measure onto a hot greased griddle. Spread to make 4-inch pancakes.
Brown on each side.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: no peep cake
directions: Stir together the first 4 ingredients. Add the frosting. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Do not Peep!!! Cook in Bundt pan. Let cool in pan for 30 minutes.

title: easy burritos
directions: Fry potatoes with onion in oil. Brown meat and add all seasoning. Mix potatoes, meat, tomato sauce and jalapenos. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Fill tortillas with meat mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Toss Croutettes stuffing mix with melted margarine; set aside for topping.
Prepare broccoli according to your liking (suggest 10 minutes in microwave).
Should be tender.
Set side.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease baking dish and line with thin layer of bread crumbs. Cook broccoli according to directions until tender.
Drain well. Cover bread crumbs with a layer of broccoli, then a layer of bread crumbs, then a layer of broccoli.
Melt the butter with Cheez Whiz.
Stir and pour over broccoli. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, saving 1 cup crumbs to put on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges in food chopper.
Add sugar. Blend well.
Refrigerate.

title: k c ground round vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot. Simmer covered for one hour.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Cool.
Mix icing and sliced thawed strawberries.
Punch holes in cake and spread icing over cake.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix up last 3 ingredients; pour over vegetables and let stand 1 hour.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Mix together in large bowl sugar, flour and salt.
Add boiled ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla, soda and sour cream.
Pour into a greased 18 x 12 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift into a mixing bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add peanut butter. Blend with a fork. Stir in milk and egg. Spoon into a buttered loaf pan, 9 x 5-inches. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: peachy-almond muffins
directions: Chop peaches; drain and set aside.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a mixing bowl; make a well in the center of dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil; stir until moistened.
Add peaches and remaining ingredients; stir until blended.
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin cups, filling about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes for 12 regular size muffins.

title: tater gravy
directions: Fry bacon in iron frying pan.
When done, remove bacon.
Add potato cubes; cook until brown.
Remove potatoes.
Add flour to remaining grease.
Brown flour; add salt and pepper and potatoes. Stir; add water and cook until gravy is thick.
Pour into thick bowl and crumble bacon on top of gravy.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Use one very large bowl and an electric mixer or use a food processor.
You will also need a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan and patience to keep from peeking in the oven.

title: baked chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of shrimp soup
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil.
Thicken with a white sauce of flour and milk.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix batter as any other cake.
Cut dates and orange slices and use 1/2 cup flour on these.
Bake in a tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours to 2 3/4 hours.

title: elaine's company chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put mixture in baking pan. Add chicken, cut up, and cover with aluminum foil. Cook 2 hours at 250° or 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove about 15 minutes before done.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook over low heat and stir until dissolved.
Cook until a little syrup dropped into cold water forms a soft ball.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until thick and creamy.
Thin with a small amount of milk, if necessary.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Cook 3/4 cup butter and Marshmallow Creme in Dutch oven over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth.
Beat cooked sweet potatoes, marshmallow mixture, eggs, sugar and milk at medium speed with an electric mixer, in batches, until smooth, stopping occasionally to scrape down sides.
Spoon into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Melt 1/3 cup butter and brown sugar in a small saucepan over low heat.
Let cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cereal and pecans.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until browned.
Makes 10 servings.

title: vinegar pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly. Combine water, vinegar and egg. Beat well with fork. Add shortening. Stir well.
Chill 2 hours before using.
Makes enough for a large cobbler.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown vegetables.
Add meat and brown.
Add beans and heat through.
Divide up mixture on 10 shells.
Fold over shells.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or larger.
Pour enchilada sauce on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Bake uncovered.

title: golden wedding punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl.
"Float" orange sherbet in mixture.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Heat pineapple with dry Jell-O. When dissolved, cool, then add buttermilk and stir. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain can of pineapple chunks and put juice in large bowl. Mix in pudding until well blended.
Drain fruit cocktail and Mandarin oranges well. Throw juice away.
Add all fruit to pudding mixture.
Last, add Cool Whip and mix well.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: lefse
directions: Clean and wash trout.
Remove heat and tail, if desired.
Line a large sheet pan with foil, leaving enough foil to wrap fish in. Place about 1/2 cup of oleo on foil.
Mix remaining ingredients. Roll fish in the mixture and lay on the foil.
Place bacon over fish with lemon slices.
Roll foil, completely covering fish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ice cream crunch pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; remove from heat.
Stir in Marshmallow Creme quickly.
Add cereal.
Press into buttered 9-inch pie pan, building up edge.
Chill.
Fill with ice cream.

title: my mother's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time (this is very important to lightness).
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Beat at low speed until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry or already made pastry. Beat egg slightly with rotary beater.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: three-layer pie
directions: Mix and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown; cool.

title: feta chicken(yield:  4-6 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: tangy barbecue chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Dip chicken in sauce.
Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with aluminum foil.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Occasionally dip sauce over chicken.
While cooking, keep chicken well covered with foil. Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into prepared shell.
Top with 2 cups pecans, chopped.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cook chicken in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly on top of stove.
Serve over rice.

title: stir-fry sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Will freeze into 3 or 4 servings.
To use, thaw one serving.
Cut meat (chicken, pork, beef) into narrow slices.
Marinate meat in sauce while preparing vegetables (peas, broccoli, etc.).

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and let stand while mixing other ingredients, then add drained raisins and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in butter, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes, or until toasted.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Freeze in electric ice cream freezer.
Let ripen at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate mint kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar gradually and cream of tartar; beat until stiff.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Spoon meringue into piping bag fitted with 1-inch round tip.
Pipe meringue kisses onto foil-lined baking sheets.
Bake at 250° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm to touch and lightly browned. Makes 3 dozen.

title: white sauce
directions: Mix butter, flour and milk in a saucepan.
Cook until thick. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add chopped, boiled eggs and bologna.
Serve hot on toast or white bread.
To make thicker or thinner, subtract or add 1 tablespoon butter or flour.
Milk stays the same.

title: american indian fry bread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients and add warm water to form soft dough. Put aside for 2 to 3 hours, then the dough can be kneaded for a minute and rolled out on a floured board. Cut dough into pieces (doughnut shaped) and fry until brown.
Goes good with chili.

title: grilled teriyaki pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
For marinade, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour half of marinade into large glass dish.
Place chops in marinade; pour remaining marinade over chops.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a large saucepan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine, salt and cream of tartar.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, add baking soda and beat mixture down.
Pour over popped corn, stirring gently until all corn is covered.
Spread coated corn on two greased cookie sheets and bake one hour at 200°.
Cool.
Break apart and enjoy.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except noodles and cheese. Layer noodles, sauce and cheese in 2 layers. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Flatten each biscuit or unroll crescent rolls.
Wrap each around a wiener letting end of wiener peep out.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450 degrees.

title: very good brownies
directions: Bake in large pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: langley's favorite chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Mix together sour cream and chicken soup.
Layer in casserole dish half of the chicken,
half of the soup mixture, remaining chicken, then remaining soup mixture. Place the crushed Ritz crackers on top of casserole; dot with margarine.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces and season to taste with pepper and garlic salt.
Marinate for several hours in equal portions of soy sauce, whiskey and cooking oil.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and water. Cook 5 minutes. Add lemon and butter, few drops of yellow food coloring if desired. Put sauce in 2 qt. baking dish.

title: fiesta guacamole dip
directions: In small bowl, combine refried beans and chiles; spread on large serving plate.
Combine sour cream and taco seasoning; spoon over bean mixture, spreading evenly.

title: homemade chicken noodles or dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone and cut into bite sized pieces.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and salt together.
Add flour to make a thick dough.
Roll out dough on floured surface until very thin.
Cut into 1/2 inch strips.
Dry for 20 minutes and drop a few at a time into rapidly boiling chicken broth.
Cook until tender.
Then add
milk and soup.
Bring to a boil and add chopped chicken.
Serve.

title: bean and bacon soup
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in drippings until onion begins to color.
Add canned vegetables and bacon.
Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp snackies(appetizer)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread on 1/2-inch slices of French bread.
Bake in 450° oven until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.

title: double chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt semi-sweet chips with 2/3 cup Eagle Brand, 1 tablespoon cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 cup walnuts.
Spread evenly into foil-lined 9-inch square pan.

title: spence's lemon cookies
directions: Combine mix, Cool Whip and egg.
Grease cookie sheets.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in sugar; roll to coat.
Put 1 1/2 inches apart on sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese, Jell-O and hot water in a mixing bowl. Blend well with an electric mixer.
All the cheese should be dissolved.
Add cold water, pineapple and nuts.
Blend and then pour mixture into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: hearty navy bean soup
directions: Sort and rinse navy beans.
Combine beans with enough water to cover by 2-inches in a stockpot.
Bring beans to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Let stand, covered, for 1 hour; drain well.

title: squash casserole 6
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Add butter, salt, pepper, pimento and milk and mix.
Then add well beaten eggs, onion, cheese and cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Serves about 8.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Drain. Place beef in casserole dish, then the Tater Tots. Top with soup and cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 1 hour.

title: ellen's broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix onion, soup, eggs, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Stir in chopped broccoli.
Pour into greased oblong baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Mix Ritz cracker crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; beat in egg.
Put baking soda in soup and add to the creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and spices together and add to creamed mixture.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan at 375° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean (about 35 minutes).

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Blend egg yolks, butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: basic muffins
directions: Grease muffin pans.
Combine dry ingredients in a medium bowl, mixing well.
Blend in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

title: sausage stuffed loaf
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until pink is gone.
Set aside.
In same skillet cook beef, onion and green pepper until beef is no longer pink.
Drain; stir in tomato, tomato sauce and seasonings. Cut sausages in half lengthwise and slice; add to meat sauce.
Cut a wedge out of top of bread (about 2 inches) wide and 3/4 of the way through loaf.
Fill loaf with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Wrap in heavy duty foil and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy southern-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large roasting pan, melt butter. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
On waxed paper, crush stuffing mix.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in stuffing mixture to coat.
Arrange chicken in a single layer in pan.
Bake 20 minutes; turn chicken and bake 20 minutes longer or until tender and golden brown.

title: un-italian meat sauce and spaghetti
directions: In medium-sized stew pot, brown ground meat fully.
Drain off fat.
With burner on medium heat, return meat to pot.
Add tomato paste and 3 cans of water per can of paste (9 cans water total). Stir until mixed fairly well.
Add mushrooms, Worcestershire, salt and chili powder.
Cook on medium until it comes to a boil, then lower heat and simmer for at least 30 minutes, preferably more than 1 hour.

title: coconut cake and icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add vanilla, milk and flour until all is used.
Pour in 3 cake pans.
Spray with Pam or grease and flour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: While macaroni is cooking, thicken milk with cornstarch. Stir constantly to prevent scorching so it will not be lumpy.
Melt cheese in sauce.

title: wine chicken
directions: Mix in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan the rice, soup and wine. Lay chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: cloved onions
directions: Peel and cook fresh onions until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter with cloves in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Add onions and stir gently until coated.
Sprinkle brown sugar over onions; cook, turning frequently, about 5 minutes until onions are golden and glazed.

title: potato tots and bacon
directions: Wrap frozen potato tots in 1/2 strip bacon and bake in 400° oven until bacon is crisp.

title: cheesy ravioli bake
directions: Brown meat; drain. Place spaghetti sauce, meat and mushrooms in a bowl. Boil water for ravioli; drain. Place ravioli in bowl with sauce, mushrooms and meat. Stir well. Place in a casserole dish and cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese has melted. Yield: 6 servings.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cut franks in thirds diagonally. Brown in butter.
Add noodles.
Pour sauce over moistening all. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, 25 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in one can of water.
Add bouillon, broth and mushrooms to onion. Bring to a boil.
Pour over rice in casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon delight
directions: Take flour, margarine and 1/2 pecans and mix together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° and cool.
Take 1 cup Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar and mix together. Spread over crust.
Then put pudding and milk, mixed together until thick, over second layer.
Spread the rest of Cool Whip on top.

title: cinnamon coffeecake
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and shortening; mix until crumbly. Reserve 1/2 cup to sprinkle over the batter.
To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, soda and cinnamon and mix thoroughly.
Add milk and eggs and mix well.

title: homemade peanut butter
directions: Place ingredients in an electric blender.
Blend until mixture becomes paste like or spreadable.
It may be necessary to add more peanuts.
The ingredients must be blended for several minutes. Store in tightly covered container.
Homemade peanut butter will separate on standing. Stir before using.

title: chicken-in-a-packet
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Cut four 20-inch long pieces of foil. Divide and layer tomatoes, onions, mushrooms, peppers and potatoes on each foil piece. Place a chicken breast on each vegetable nest. Mix Worcestershire sauce and pepper in a small bowl. Spoon over each chicken breast. Top with 1 teaspoon margarine and 1 teaspoon honey.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar together for 20 minutes; add eggs, beating in one at a time.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Add lemon extract and fold in 7-Up.
Pour into well-greased 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes. Remove from oven and cool on wire rack for 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.
