title: mint-chocolate chip ice milk
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together the sugar and gelatin. Stir in evaporated skim milk.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until sugar and gelatin dissolve and mixture almost boils; remove from heat.
In a small bowl, slightly beat egg white and egg. Stir about 1/2 cup of the hot gelatin mixture into the eggs; return all to saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat 2 minutes more.
Do not boil.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups skim milk, creme de menthe and vanilla.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator for 1 hour. Stir food coloring into cooled milk mixture, if desired.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate.
Freeze mixture in a 4 to 5-quart ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's directions.
Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: In a deep baking dish or pan, cream margarine and sugar.
Mix in milk, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Pour fruit in on top of crust and spread it out.
Place in a 350° oven.
Crust will rise, covering the fruit.
Let crust brown.

title: bob l's favorite sweet n' sour turkey
directions: Cook green beans as directed on package. Drain.
In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar and cornstarch. Stir in vinegar, reserved pineapple liquid and margarine. Cook until sauce boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Stir in pineapple chunks, turkey, tomato halves and green beans.
Continue to cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally. Serve over hot cooked rice. Garnish with sesame seed, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in order given (4-quart salad bowl). Toss mushrooms with lemon juice before layering.
Top with peas. Spread mayo as frosting over all.
Seal to edges of bowl. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Toss.

title: classic cocoa sauce
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in a saucepan.
Blend in evaporated milk.
Add butter and salt.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture just begins to boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla. Serve warm over ice cream or other desserts.
Great over hot fudge cake.
Makes about 2 cups of sauce.

title: sourdough starter mix
directions: Mix in crock and set in warm place 24 hours.
Use amount needed and place remainder in refrigerator.
When needed, set out to warm.
Add 1 cup of flour and 1 cup of water and let set in warm place overnight.
With care, this starter can be kept working for several years.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine grated apple and sugars.
Let stand 20 to 30 minutes. Combine flour, soda and cinnamon; add apple mixture, oil, egg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pimento and cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese.
Chop pimentos and add mayonnaise, lemon and garlic; mix well.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Pour cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple (mixed together) in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with 1 box cake mix.
Slice 2 sticks of margarine over cake mix.
Cover with 1 cup chopped nuts. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo; save half.
Mix remaining 1/2 oleo in corn.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and bring to boil, then simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
May be doubled.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Heat milk nearly to boiling point.
Add corn meal.
Beat egg yolks and add to milk and corn meal.
Add margarine, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into rest of ingredients.
Bake in a greased dish at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: fruity soft ice cream
directions: Place whipping cream, dry milk and sugar in blender container. Cover and blend on high speed 10 seconds.
Add about 1/2 cup of raspberries.
Cover and blend on high speed 10 seconds; stir. Repeat with remaining raspberries, about 1/2 cup at a time.
Serve immediately or for firmer consistency, freeze 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wassail
directions: Combine the ingredients (except for the apple cider). Bring to a boil and simmer for about 20 minutes. Add apple cider. Remove cloves and cinnamon sticks, using cheese cloth or strainer. Keep mixture warm in crock-pot or kettle. Makes 4 quarts.

title: raw vegetable pizza
directions: Cover bottom of pan (11 x 17-inch) with crescent rolls stretched to fit pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until brown.
Let cool thoroughly.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all in blender.
Blend until smooth and store in refrigerator where it will thicken as it sets.
1 1/8 c. = to 15 oz. can sweetened condensed milk.

title: speedy rolls
directions: Stir the water, sugar, salt and yeast to dissolve yeast.
Add the eggs, shortening and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Add 4 cups sifted flour and knead until smooth.
Let rise.
Punch down.
Shape into buns.
Let rise.
Makes about 4 dozen rolls, small size.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: blt dip
directions: Cook bacon in the microwave until fairly crisp.
Mix together the sour cream and miracle whip.
Then mix together all of the other ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2-3 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers or cut-up toasted white or wheat bread.

title: vivian whittington's sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown crumbled sausage in a skillet; drain.
In a large bowl, mix celery, onion, soups, water and rice.
Add sausage and mix. Pour into casserole.
Cover and bake 2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Poke holes in cake while hot.
Mix 2 cups powdered sugar and juice of 2 lemons (5 to 6 tablespoons) and pour over cake.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Place vegetables in plastic bag or shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover. Marinate in refrigerator 6 hours or overnight.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture forms a ball. This play dough smells great and is less crumbly than other types.

title: homemade bubbles
directions: The longer you store this, the better it works.
Prepare weeks or months in advance for special events.
Cut off tops and bottoms of coffee cans.
Smooth the edges of cans.
Dip can in pan of solution.
Wave through the air!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole with stuffing
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions.
Add egg and baking powder when cooled.
Cook all vegetables together until tender. Add chicken and gravy.
Season to taste.
Place all in casserole dish and top with stuffing mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through and stuffing is brown.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Brown wings lightly in olive oil and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Drain wings and put in mixture, coat well.
Put in single layer in foil-lined pan and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until well done.
Do not turn.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients together.
Beat the vinegar, egg and water together and add to the flour mixture.
Mix all together well.
Chill dough for at least 15 minutes before rolling a crust.

title: chicken every sunday
directions: Dip chicken into melted butter or margarine.
Mix soups with water; pour over rice in a casserole dish.
Arrange chicken on top.
Cook, uncovered, at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Turn higher the last 15 minutes (375°) for browning.

title: salsa
directions: Mix and chill several hours before serving.
If desired, can salsa by cold packing and process pints 35 minutes.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Mix and pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook cabbage with onion and butter.
Boil kluski noodles. Mix the noodles with the cabbage.
Cut up bacon or ham.
Add to cabbage and noodle mixture.
Cook 1 hour.

title: "captain's catfish stew"
directions: Prepare catfish for stew.
Put fish in big pot with remainder of ingredients and cook until tender and done.
Heavenly!

title: special rice krispie treat
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips in microwave at medium setting for 3 minutes. Stir to blend and mix in Rice Krispies. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm. Cut into squares.

title: sun dried tomato pesto
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender or food processor and mix. Pesto should be chunky. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: ginger pumpkin mousse
directions: In small bowl, beat egg yolks (on high) and 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy (approximately 5 minutes). Transfer yolk mixture to saucepan. Whisk in milk, pumpkin, spices and orange peel.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until boils (approximately 5 minutes).	Remove and put mixture in large bowl. Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Place layer of crackers on foil. Boil oleo and sugar until foamy.
Dribble over crackers and bake at 325° for about 12 minutes.
Cover with chocolate chips and put back into oven until melted.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Sift flour with cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder.
In medium bowl, combine lemon peel, zucchini and walnuts.

title: lora's muffins
directions: Take boiling water and pour over oatmeal, bran cereal and Shredded Wheat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix in large bowl. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
This can be mixed and left in refrigerator for up to a month.
Just take out wheat you need and bake.

title: short ribs
directions: Brown short ribs on all sides in oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add water, bouillon cubes, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and onions.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Measure cooking liquid and, if necessary, add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Thicken with flour for gravy.

title: toasted cheese on ritz crackers
directions: Beat together.
Spoon on Ritz crackers.
Put under broiler until bubbly.
Watch that they don't burn.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Heat 1/2 of oil in skillet and fry tortillas about 15 seconds each side.
Remove and pat off excess oil.
In separate skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of oil and saute onion until tender.
Add chilies, garlic, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Add shredded beef.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Dip tortillas in egg. Fill with sauce mixture,
roll and place in shallow greased baking dish.
Pour enchilada sauce over tortillas.
Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sour cream. Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole.
Mix all ingredients (onions chopped fine) and pour over margarine.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Place 1/4 of the chicken in the middle of each tortilla.
Top with 1 tablespoon of sour cream.
Fold up both sides of the tortilla so they overlap in the middle.
Place tortillas, seam side down, in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with salsa and cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with remaining sour cream before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend together oil, sugar, eggs, zucchini and vanilla in blender.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake in two greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pumpkin-maple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare piecrust according to package directions for a single-crust pie, using a 9-inch pie pan.
Whisk together pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, maple syrup, cinnamon, ginger and maple extract until smooth.
Pour into prepared piecrust.
Bake pie 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes, or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean.
Transfer pie to wire rack and cool completely.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place popped corn in large roasting pan; let stand in oven while preparing glaze.
In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Without stirring, boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over warm popcorn; toss to coat well.
Bake 60 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool, stirring frequently.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat all together and stir in all dry ingredients.
Bake 1 hour or until done on 350°.

title: fudge no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk and margarine for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let stand 1 hour.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add soup and heat, mixing or beating smooth.
Add sour cream, salt and pepper.
Fold in onion and cheese.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread potatoes evenly in dish. Pour saucepan mixture over potatoes, mixing lightly.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cornflake crumbs over potato mixture in casserole dish.
Dot with margarine.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven or until golden brown on top.

title: microwave twice-baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes all over with a fork.
Arrange in spoke pattern on a paper towel in oven.
Microwave on HIGH 9 to 10 minutes, turning and rearranging potatoes once, until almost tender.
Let stand 5 minutes until fork-tender.
Cut off a thin lengthwise slice from tops of potatoes.
Working over a medium-size bowl, scoop out potatoes, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells.
Add milk and butter to bowl; mash until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into shells.
Put potatoes on a microwave-safe plate and microwave on HIGH 2 to 3 minutes until filling is hot.
Sprinkle tops with additional chives and bacon.
Makes 2 servings.

title: brown sugar bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in brown sugar and rest of ingredients. Bake in 8-inch square pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snicker cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed. Pour 1/2 into greased 9 x 13 pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole no. 1
directions: Put raw chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish so that it fits comfortably.
Combine
sour cream, dry onion soup mix and mushroom soup.
Mix well and spread over chicken.
Spread with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: yeast rolls
directions: To mashed potatoes, add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs in a five quart mixing bowl and cream well.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to lukewarm milk.
Add to potato mixture.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Toss on floured board and knead well.
Put in bowl and let rise until double in bulk.

title: golden punch
directions: Heat all but ginger ale to dissolve sugar.
Put in milk jugs and freeze.
Take out of freezer 2 hours before serving, then chop and add ginger ale.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli and chop it up.
Mix soups, milk and water together and cook until well blended and heated through.
Add broccoli and cook 5 to 10 more minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese to taste just before serving.
May also add black pepper.

title: uncle ken's tartar sauce
directions: Mix well.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
Keeps real well.

title: cranberry glaze(i serve this with fresh or smoked ham)
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat; serve immediately.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Combine all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.	Serve warm with chips. (Can put in fondue or crock-pot.)

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small mixer bowl, beat eggs slightly at medium speed.
Beat in corn syrup, sugar, butter or margarine, vanilla and salt until well blended.
Stir in pecans. Spoon filling into pie shell.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, 2/3 cup sugar and salt in a double boiler top. Slowly stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thick enough to mound slightly when dropped from spoon. Cover; cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Stir a little hot mixture into beaten egg yolks; then stir all into remaining hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: no cook potato candy
directions: Work hot potato 1/4 at a time into sugar and salt until mixture is consistency of pie dough.
(May need to add more sugar.)
Roll out on waxed paper dusted with small amount of sugar.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill for several hours and then slice.
Store in covered container.
Yields 7 pounds candy or approximately 20 pieces.

title: chip dip
directions: Crumble and brown sausage; set aside.
Put Pace picante sauce in saucepan, get hot then chunk cheese in until all is melted, then add sausage and stir good.
Makes a good party dip.

title: pork roast
directions: This can be preboiled to hasten cooking or bake in a 250° oven until tender.
Mix 1/2 and 1/2 honey and 57 sauce.
Add 2 or 3 tablespoons mustard.
Mix.
Cut meat in serving size pieces.
Pour mixture over meat and cook about 30 to 45 minutes longer (enough to get taste cooked into meat).

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix graham crackers, oleo, peanut butter and powdered sugar together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Spread over the top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: What could be better for a casual supper at home than juicy burgers.
For a change of pace, try this burger made with added sauce or seasonings.

title: cocktail meatball sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat in large pot.

title: meatless lasagna
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain, return to pot and fill with cold water. Cover bottom of large baking pan with tomato sauce.
Add 4 eggs and parsley to Ricotta.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Place all ingredients except the cheese and meat in a blender and mix for a few seconds to blend well.
Pour into greased 9 or 10-inch pie or quiche pan.
Sprinkle cheese and meat over the top, pushing gently below the surface with the back of a spoon.
Pan will be full to the rim.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Allow to cool.
Set at room temperature before cutting and serving.

title: fish baked in wine
directions: Any white fish, sole, halibut, sea bass, catfish, or salmon may be used.

title: tomato-herb bread salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the tomatoes, celery, scallions, lemon zest, garlic, basil, parsley and mint.
Add the olive oil, white wine vinegar, salt and pepper and mix well.
Slice the bread in half lengthwise.
Pour on enough water to completely moisten the bread.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Squeeze out the excess water.
Finely chop the bread and toss it in the salad.
Season with additional salt and pepper if needed.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: corn dish casserole
directions: Melt butter in large baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Spread over bottom and halfway up sides, while oven is preheating to 350°.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat in egg. Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk to sugar mixture, blend thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
For a sugary top, lightly flatten each cookie with bottom of glass which has been buttered and then dipped into the sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet while hot.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: mom's easy chili hot dish
directions: Mix well and heat through.

title: amish cookies
directions: Mix oil, butter and sugars well.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Then add remaining ingredients and blend well. Spoon onto greased cookie sheet and flatten with glass dipped in powdered sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Toss vegetables and eggs together.
Chill before serving. Toss with Garlic Dressing.

title: chinese meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except gravy and water chestnuts. Brown, then simmer in canned mushroom gravy.
Add sliced water chestnuts.
Serve.

title: easy family pot pie(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Mix and pour into any flat baking pan, large Pyrex or cake pan. Roll to pan size and trim or tuck excess crust into sides.
Pierce with fork in several places.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until mixture is bubbly and crust is golden brown.

title: custard pie
directions: Prepare pastry. Chill thoroughly. Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar and salt. Slowly stir in hot scalded milk. Add vanilla and mix well. Pour mixture into pastry shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 425° or until custard is firm.

title: yummy apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Toss lightly to mix.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Dot with butter.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Scoop out pulp of baked potatoes.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually add 6 cups of milk. Cook until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Add pulp, salt, pepper, onions and bacon.
Add 1 cup of cheese.
Stir in sour cream and more milk, if too thick.
Garnish with remaining cheese.

title: tuna roll
directions: Saute onions, celery and peppers in butter.
Cook until light brown.
Remove from head and add tuna and 1 cup white sauce.
Mix well.
Spread filling onto biscuit rectangle.
Roll jelly roll fashion and cut into 1 inch slices.
Put in 9x13-inch greased pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and put remaining sauce on top.
Grate added cheese on top if you want. Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Remove and allow to cool 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hamburger and cheese pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper. Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic salt and salt. Simmer while preparing crust.

title: best gingersnaps
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, egg and molasses and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Roll into balls; roll balls in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: gumdrop bars
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs and add the sugar and vanilla. Mix in the flour, salt, walnuts and half of the gumdrops.
Pour this mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the remaining gumdrops on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes until the top forms into a light crust.
Remove from oven and cool slightly on a rack.
Cut the bars with a greased knife.
Remove carefully from the pan.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over medium heat until mixture starts to thicken.
Stir often.

title: crescent tuna cups
directions: Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Press dough around the bottom and up the edges of muffin tins.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon mixture into dough-lined cups.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: banana split salad
directions: Stir together honey, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add pineapple, oranges and coconut; toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Arrange in 4 servings between banana halves. Garnish with apple and cherries.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill crock-pot with sliced cooking apples.
Add ingredients. Cook on high until tender.
Then turn down on low and simmer 24 hours.
Use a mixer and mix until very smooth.
Fill jars while hot.
During the last few hours, you may crack the lid so the apple butter will get thicker.
This also makes very good fried apple pies, almost as good as dried apples, without all the hard work.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook altogether at 250° for 5 hours or 350° for 2 hours.
Add no water.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Blend flour, milk and Velveeta cheese.
Then add to broccoli.
Stir until soup thickens.
Add 2 cubes chicken bouillon (or cook in broccoli).
Add half and half and pepper to taste.

title: mountain high cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour batter into cake pans.
Make 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: dipped-applesauce sandwiches(diet)
directions: Blend applesauce and cinnamon.
Spread over 4 slices of bread. Top with
4 remaining slices.
Beat egg whites, milk
and salt in a shallow dish.
Dip sandwiches in egg mixture to coat.
Brown on both sides in low-fat butter in skillet.

title: hot sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Remove sausage from casings.
Cook in large skillet, breaking up the meat with fork until no longer pink, about 8 to 10 minutes. Drain off fat.
Spoon sausage into large bowl and cool completely.
Add cheese, biscuit mix and water; mix with fork until blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on large cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until browned.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool completely on wire racks.
Makes 120 puffs.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Mix all ingredients together. Let set for 2 hours before serving.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups or 10 servings.

title: 1, 2, 3 peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Roll into small balls; place on a greased cookie sheet and press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
As easy as 1,2,3.

title: macaroni and cheese beef bake
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner according to directions. Brown ground beef and onion in frypan and drain off excess fat. Combine thoroughly remaining ingredients with beef mixture and macaroni dinner.
Season to taste and place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: blt egg bake
directions: Spread mayonnaise on one side of each slice of toast and cut into small pieces.
Arrange toast, mayonnaise side up, in a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with cheese slices and bacon.
In a skillet, fry eggs over medium heat until completely set; place over bacon.
Top with tomato slices; set aside.
In a sauce pan, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Pour over tomato.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 325 degrees for 10 minutes.
Cut into squares; serve with lettuce.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: pork chops in corn
directions: Brown seasoned chops on both sides.
Drain off excess fat. Arrange chops along sides of a 5 to 6-cup shallow baking dish. Mix crumbs, milk, corn, eggs, onion and seasonings in pan used to brown chops.
Do not wash the skillet after browning chops.
Mix thoroughly and pour into pan covering chops.
Bake in 325° oven for about 45 minutes or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: marshall field's cranberry nut muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and sugar.
Blend in margarine.
Add eggs, water and orange juice concentrate.
With an electric mixer, beat batter at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add pecans and cranberries.
Mix until well-distributed.
Fill lightly greased muffin tins with batter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove muffins from tins and cool completely on a wire rack.
Make 24 muffins.

title: good quick doughnuts
directions: Cut centers of biscuits for making doughnuts.
(You can use a regular doughnut cutter for this.)
Fry in heated cooking oil. Fry until golden brown on each side.
Centers may also be fried. They are just as good.
After frying, turn on confectioners sugar and you have a good bit of taste.
Also, try putting the fried doughnuts in a brown paper sack with the confectioners sugar; shake well and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese set until at room temperature, then mix all ingredients except pecans.
Roll
into ball, then roll ball in pecans until outside is covered.

title: egg-sausage brunch bake
directions: Sprinkle half the cheese in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Beat eggs and pour over cheese; add salt and pepper. Add cream. Sprinkle sausage over all and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: marshmallow peanut butter sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on one slice of bread.
On the other slice of bread spread Marshmallow Creme.
Put slices together.

title: wendy's pimento cheese
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth, then add drained pimento, mayonnaise, Braswell's, salt, pepper and chives.
Blend that mixture with electric mixer until smooth.
Add shredded cheese last.
Serve on either crackers or croissants.

title: pearl's famous apple dish
directions: Wash and core apples.
Peel.
Cut into wedges and place into baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, grated cheese, melted margarine and salt. Press this mixture over apples to make crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: split second shrimp and snap pea salad
directions: Combine oil, mustard, lemon, celery seed and a dash of pepper.
Chill in refrigerator.
In a medium saucepan, combine onion, bay leaves, peppercorns and 4 cups water.
Bring to boil. Then reduce heat and add shrimp.
simmer 3 minutes.
Drain and cover, then chill.
Remove strings from snap peas.
Cook peas until crisp-tender and chill.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then add the syrup, rum and brandy.
Mix thoroughly and chill for a few hours in refrigerator. Remove and roll into small balls not more than 1-inch in diameter.
Should make about 60 balls. Roll the balls in sifted confectioners sugar and store for a few days in a tightly covered tin box. These improve with age.

title: caramel-filled chocolate cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.	Combine flour, soda and cocoa; gradually add to butter mixture, beating well.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
Cover and chill dough at least 2 hours.
(Dough is easier to handle if you can chill for longer than 2 hours or put in the freezer for a while to get it firm enough to handle.
You want to be able to wrap it around the Rolo without all the dough sticking to your hands.) Combine remaining 1/2 cup pecans and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Divide dough into 4 equal portions.

Work with 1 portion at a time, storing remainder in refrigerator.	Divide each portion into 12 pieces (I try to use a heaping teaspoon full for each cookie). Quickly press each piece of dough around a caramel; roll into a ball.
Dip one side of ball in pecan mixture.
Place balls, pecan side up, 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cookies will look soft.
Let cool 1 minute on cookie sheets; remove to wire racks and let cool completely. Yield:
4 dozen.

title: oriental green beans
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Drain.
Heat remaining ingredients, except almonds. Add to green beans.
Stir to blend.
Place in serving dish and sprinkle almonds over top. Makes 6 servings.

title: peppery cajun stir-fry
directions: Trim and discard fat from thighs and cut them into thin strips. In medium sized bowl, toss chicken with Italian seasoning and red, black and white pepper.
In large wok or nonstick skillet over medium heat, heat oil.
Add seasoned chicken and stir-fry about 3 minutes or until just cooked through.
Add scallions and cut peppers; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce.
Cook 1 minute longer or until chicken is nicely brown.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve over brown rice.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees with two iron skillets with 3 tbsp oil in each skillet.
While the pans heat, mix corn meal with 3 eggs & milk to make a cornbread mixture.
Pour in hot pans & bake until firm & brown.
Heat broth to a boil while bread is cooking. Put bread in large pan and put onions & celery on the bread & pour on hot broth.
Mix & stir hot broth.
Mix real well until mixed good.
Add eggs & pepper and put in buttered pyrex dishes & spread also on top.
Bake at 350 degrees until firm and begins to brown. About 1 hour.
Makes 3 pyrex 9x13-inch dishes.

title: peach ripple coffee cake
directions: Generously grease 12-cup glass Bundt cake pan.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and cinnamon, coat dish.
Mix baking mix, sugar, milk and eggs; stir vigorously 30 strokes.
Fold in peaches. Spread 3 cups of batter in dish.
Mix 1/2 cup of remaining batter and the apple butter; spoon over batter in dish.
Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls onto apple butter mixture.
Place dish on inverted dinner plate in oven.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cool.
Mix lettuce, onions, beans, olives and cheese.
Add ground beef and mix in bottle of dressing.
Crush bag of Fritos and mix into salad.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place diced, cooked chicken in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain
tuna.
In large bowl mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour
mixture into a greased casserole dish. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine. Set aside. Mix all puddings and milk and let set up.

title: virginia chunk pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in cold water and salt for 7 days.
Stir every morning so as not to get a scum.
On the eighth day, drain and rinse.
Soak for 24 hours in 1 gallon cold water to 2 tablespoons alum.
Drain well.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: To chilled macaroni, add all the ingredients.
Mix well. Chill and serve.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine egg, molasses, sugar and Crisco.
Dissolve baking soda in water; add to batter with rest of ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Wash the sausage in hot water and drain.
Set aside.

title: dump cake
directions: Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: tomato-topped fish
directions: Thaw fish.
Arrange in single layer in greased baking dish. Season with salt and pepper.
Slice or chop tomato and layer on fish.
Combine bread crumbs, margarine, cheese and parsley in a small bowl.
Sprinkle over tomatoes.
Bake in 400°
oven about 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: madelyn's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown garlic in oil; add hamburg.
Add peppers, onions, celery and water
and
simmer.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 2 to 3 hours on
low heat, stirring often.
Serve on spaghetti, macaroni or on scrambled eggs.
Add mushrooms, if wanted.

title: rice dressing
directions: Brown meat, stirring often.
Add other ingredients and simmer until tender.
Add rice to meat mixture and mix well.

title: tropical fruit bars
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar; cook until it bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, Add K and coconut.
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Cool and slice into squares.

title: chocolate-cherry layer cake
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture thickens and boils.
Pour hot thickened juice over 3 cups canned, pitted drained cherries.
Set aside.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Combine water, seafood seasoning, vinegar and sugar and bring to a boil.
Divide frozen haddock into 4 sections.
Add to boiling mixture and boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with hot melted butter. Serves 2 to 4.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Stir together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.
For sheet cake, bake 45 minutes; 2-layer cake, bake for 35 minutes and for tube pan, bake 55 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: polynesian ginger dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Trim top with additional candied ginger bits.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Bake the pie crust as directed.
Mix 1/2 cup cocoa, 1/2 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar in a small bowl.
Add water to make a paste. Separate the eggs.
Combine the egg yolks, paste, 2-1/2 cups of sugar and margarine.
Cook on low heat stirring constantly until the mixture thickens.
Pour 1/2 the mixture in each pie crust.

title: hearty italian bean soup
directions: Cut ham into small pieces; dice celery, carrots, onion and zucchini.
Mash beans with fork until smooth.
In medium saucepot, heat oil.
Cook ham, celery, onion, carrots, zucchini, basil and pepper until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes, chicken broth, beans and 1 can water over high heat until boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add pasta.
Serve with Romano grated cheese.
